text:
i’m only showing one set tonight because tonight was a rough night. i went to the gym after work because i always struggle with the winter darkness and 3:15am alarms this time of year. i figured i’d try out the 7pm workout and see if it’s something i could tolerate until springtime. .
my warmups were going nicely until someone approached me and struck up a conversation. he wanted to know if i recorded videos to make money on youtube or if i was doing them for myself. i politely explained i record videos to check my form and see how the weight is moving. what seemed as an innocent question instantly turned into sexual harassment. .
he took my willingness to answer his question as some sort of invitation to make inappropriate comments about my body, my shape, my muscular build, and how he found me sexy af (repeated that one a few times). he went on to say that for a girl he sees as plus size, i’m sexy to him, but it’s okay that he says that because “hey look me, i’m not exactly thin”. he went on to talk about how plus size women can dress how they want if he finds them sexy, and as if he thought i needed his approval, called me sexy one more time. .
i tried to deflect this conversation. i saw a couple of trainers i usually see in the morning and made a loud joke about how they’re following me just to get this guy away from me. it worked. he got distracted and walked away but he didn’t stop with his constant staring and desire to make awkward eye contact with me. .
he knew what he was doing. he’s likely done this before. there’s no way i’m the first, he’s a white male, mid-60s. .
i filed a complaint. i don’t deserve to be treated this way. i’ve left gyms because of this behavior before. i’m not running anymore. i’ve built up a sense of community at my gym. i shouldn’t have to adjust my workouts to avoid him. this should never have happened. the staff was professional and addressed this immediately. i’m so grateful for them. .
enough is enough. 
#metoo #enoughisenough #westsidebarbell #powerlifting #powerliftingwomen #gwpl

text:
porque nos quedamos en el relato del morbo y todavía no hablamos de lo que pasa con la persona abusada después del suceso. todavia no decimos que la persona cambió, ya no es la misma, ya no piensa igual, no ama igual, no demuestra igual. los lentes con los que veía el mundo ya no están y no estarán nunca más.
tratamos de minimizar o naturalizar el abuso en ese momento porque el shock es tan grande que no podríamos seguir el día a día. y cuando todo nuestro cuerpo grita que no está bien y que no es natural, lo decimos. para cada una es diferente. una vez que lo decimos, si nuestro alrededor no nos da contención, empezamos a pensar que quizás algo hicimos mal, sino porqué no nos entenderían? buscamos justificativos, algo que hicimos quizás fue lo que causó todo. y cambiamos nuestra forma de ser, de mostrarnos, de expresarnos. esto trae muchas consecuencias, de salud, de relaciones. claro, luego somos más fuertes, si tuvimos la oportunidad de trabajar sobre eso y aprender. pero lo que pasó pasó y está ahí siempre.
antes de dudar del testimonio, fíjate en la consecuencia del mismo, justo ahí, en la vida del abusado. las huellas están ahí. #miracomonosponemos #timesup #metoo vos sos amor 💕que no te digan lo contrario

text: reflecting on a few weeks into 32... gratitude! 31 had a rough start: my turn with #metoo, bullying, heartbreak, a little grief, coping and cycles of anxiety. life! among it all still, moments of total joy, connection and giving of myself to y’all. last year was a series of annoying lessons—wiping out and tumbling in the water, repeating mistakes learning some too. 🏄‍♀️ now it’s like i’m catching the perfect wave, and i popped up this time steady on both feet and ready for the journey to the shore. it’s a rush! i’ve got my head up, i’m balanced, i kinda know what i gotta do, i’m a little scared but open (only) to that which will enhance this beautiful ride. feeling #hashtagblessed for real to be here in good spirits, to be able, and to have so many people cheering me on 🤙 i can be 100% colleen with so many of you —even in this growth spurt— i’m so grateful. deep thanks for all the bday wishes and even more for just being in my life. 💞 we can do this when we got each other. 🌎🌍🌏

text:
mike isabella will close all his restaurants following chapter 7 bankruptcy filling,ending a year of headlines following #metoo allegations #facts dec. 13, 2018 - with a d.c. #restaurant empire in shambles following #metoo allegations and a sexual harassment lawsuit that has been settled, #mikeisabella pulled the plug on his businesses today, filing chapter 7 bankruptcy, reports #thewashingtonian the empire should close by december 27 as its assets will be liquified to pay outstanding debts; the full shutdown follows previous announcements and shutters earlier this year that saw the closures of #kapnostaverna the chef’s food stalls at nationals park, and the multi-concept #isabellaeatery isabella filed for chapter 11 #bankruptcy in september, telling the #washingtonpost at the time that “the bankruptcy is a tool for me to basically restructure my finances and have an opportunity for a fresh start.” the latest chapter 7 bankruptcy filing blamed bad press for the business’s failure: “under the present circumstances,” isabella wrote, “i am facing the sad realization that i no longer believe that any restaurant associated with my name can recover from the negative press that has enveloped me for nearly the entirety of 2018.” as the washingtonian points out, #isabella is the first chef to see his businesses totally gutted following a #metoo scandal. it’s worth noting, however, that isabella also refused to “step away” (i.e., staying out of the public eye and out of the restaurants completely, but still earning a paycheck) as chefs like #johnbesh and #mariobatali did after facing claims of sexual misconduct. it’s hard to say what the future of his well-liked restaurant brands like kapnos and graffiato would have been had he stepped away or even divested entirely

meanwhile, isabella’s business partners nick and george pagonis apparently still plan on working in d.c. hospitality. named in the now-settled sexual harassment lawsuit, the men now seem to be distancing themselves from isabella #foodninfo #foodnetwork #eater #truecooks #lefooding #dceats #huffposttaste #nyc #la #people #cheflife #tasty #michelinstar #gourmandise #eaterdenver #303eats #eaterny #eatersf

mike isabella will close all his restaurants following chapter 7 bankruptcy filling,ending a year of headlines following #metoo allegations #facts dec. 13, 2018 - with a d.c. #restaurant empire in shambles following #metoo allegations and a sexual harassment lawsuit that has been settled, #mikeisabella pulled the plug on his businesses today, filing chapter 7 bankruptcy, reports #thewashingtonian the empire should close by december 27 as its assets will be liquified to pay outstanding debts; the full shutdown follows previous announcements and shutters earlier this year that saw the closures of #kapnostaverna the chef’s food stalls at nationals park, and the multi-concept #isabellaeatery isabella filed for chapter 11 #bankruptcy in september, telling the #washingtonpost at the time that “the bankruptcy is a tool for me to basically restructure my fices and have an opportunity for a fresh start.” the latest chapter 7 bankruptcy filing blamed bad press for the business’s failure: “under the present circumstances,” isabella wrote, “i am facing the sad realization that i no longer believe that any restaurant associated with my name can recover from the negative press that has enveloped me for nearly the entirety of 2018.” as the washingtonian points out, #isabella is the first chef to see his businesses totally gutted following a #metoo scandal. it’s worth noting, however, that isabella also refused to “step away” (i.e., staying out of the public eye and out of the restaurants completely, but still earning a paycheck) as chefs like #johnbesh and #mariobatali did after facing claims of sexual misconduct. it’s hard to say what the future of his well-liked restaurant brands like kapnos and graffiato would have been had he stepped away or even divested entirely

meanwhile, isabella’s business partners nick and george pagonis apparently still plan on working in d.c. hospitality. named in the now-settled sexual harassment lawsuit, the men now seem to be distancing themselves from isabella #foodninfo #foodnetwork #eater #truecooks #lefooding #dceats #huffposttaste #nyc #la #people #cheflife #tasty #michelinstar #gourmandise #eaterdenver #303eats #eaterny #eatersf

text:
🔴penny mute on nassar🔴
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
think the miranda rights are the only cases in which the fifth amendment has been utilized? well you’d be surprised to know that the recent #metoo movement and trial of larry nassar against the usa women’s gymnastics team has incorporated elements of the fifth amendment pleas as well. like cohen, the former usa gymnastics chief, steve penny, called upon his right to plead the fifth by refusing to testify on athletes’ sexual abuse and the nassar scandal. penny stated that he was acting on the advice of his lawyers, which was to refuse to testify because it could potentially lead to his incrimination. in this case and many others, the fifth amendment continues to be extremely significant in cases involving scandals, and adds a protective barrier for the defendant to prevent exposure of other possibly incriminating information. #stevepenny #nassarscandal #pleadthefifth #fifthamendment #currentevent

text:
el pasado diciembre 11 la actriz argentina thelma fardin @soythelmafardin hizo publica la denuncia sobre acceso carnal violento contra al actor juan darthes mientras rodaba la gira de la tan popular serie “patito feo” de la cual ambos eran cast members. la actriz tendría 16 años de edad mientras que el actor (y único adulto de la gira) tendría aproximadamente 45. al momento del encuentro y antes de la violación, el actor toma su mano y la acerca a su pantalón diciendo “mira como me pones”. nueve años le tomo a su víctima reunir la fuerza para denunciarle. ahora somos un movimiento gigante latinoamericano, empoderando la acción de levantar la voz como lo hizo thelma. ha sido tan impactante para mi como espectadora y mujer quien creció viendo la televisión argentina este episodio, que hoy me uno como ilustradora a su causa. 💚 #miracomonosponemos juan. mira que ya no tenemos miedo. ya jamas nadie se saldrá con la suya. mira como nos ponemos patriarcado. #niunamas ! #noesno !. @actrices.argentinas .
•
on december 11, 2018, the argentinean teen actress thelma fardin made public a criminal complaint against actor juan darthés for abuse and rape in nicaragua in 2009, events that occurred when the actress was 16 at the time and darthés 45. before the rape, the actor takes her hand and place it in his pants saying “look how you got me”. it took nine years for the victim to gather courage and denounce his actions. now we are a huge latin american movement of people who is willing to empower the action of speaking up just like thelma did. this event has taken such an impact in me as a woman and as an spectator who grew up watching argentinian series that i today i join the cause 💚 “look how you got us”, juan. look, we are not afraid anymore. look how you got us patriarchy. #nomeansno !.

text:
traigo la fuerza, la magia, y el misterio que nos habita
.

ante los hechos actuales que nos tocan hace unos días en buenos aires, argentina, traigo esta imagen: “mujer mágica”, hecha en el verano, este año 2018, con ecos del movimiento , en ese momento nuevo, del #metoo

in the midst of some strong echoes of the #metoo movement in buenos aires argentina, these last days, i bring this "magic woman" back, to speak of our strength, our magic and the mystery which inhabit us.

text:
que salga el sol
siempre me gustó pensar que cuando llueve es porque el cielo llora. y cuando truena porque se enoja. y cuando llueve y truena porque llora y se enoja todo junto. 
hoy en buenos aires diluvió tanto que le pude ver los ojos enrojecidos al cielo. cómo lloraba. y qué impotencia tenía. esa impotencia del dolor acumulado. de la bronca contenida. de algo que lastima muy profundo. tan profundo que queda tapado. y que no hace más que seguir doliendo. 
hoy ya es mañana y el cielo sigue llorando. llora de empatía. llora con las mujeres. llora porque ya no se callan. llora por las historias que cuentan. llora porque duelen. pero el cielo no solo llora sino que también truena. y truena de enojo. enojo con los violadores. enojo con la injusticia. enojo con la indiferencia. enojo con el patriarcado que aún no se cae. enojo con los que siguen dudando. 
siempre me gustó pensar que cuando llueve es porque el cielo llora. y cuando truena porque se enoja. y cuando llueve y truena porque llora y se enoja todo junto. pero esta vez me duele. no puedo disfrutar la lluvia así. le veo al cielo cara de mujer y solo deseo que salga el sol.
.
.
.
📷: @nicobiagioni -
.
.
.

text:
what scares me the most is living in a world where people are mindlessly working as systematic machine parts for governments and corporations which profit from consumerism and the destruction of our natural environment. 
i found it incredibly moving recently to see children in australia taking to the streets to protest against our government for not taking enough action towards reducing the impact of human caused climate change despite having all of the education, information and resources made available by professionals from various industries. some children stating and asking what the point is of going to school and learning these skills when ultimately our governments ignore them in the face of profiting from huge corporations. 
is this the first time in history our youngest generations are having to gather in numbers to assert more commonsense than those in control of their own future? incredible 🌺🙏🧡 from the q&a in my stories, and a little more.

text:
this both makes me wanna laugh and cry.

because i get this cycle. i get what it feels like to be so anxious my stomach hurts, i cant eat and i feel like i'm choking on anxiety. then i go to therapy or talk to a friend and i feel a release. and i feel better!! then i either get triggered again. or i feel too good for too long and that scares me, because i'm not 'armed for the next battle or chaos' coming my way. messed up, i know. but this is anxiety. and for me this is anxiety and ptsd mixed together.

have i improved over the years?! yes! and thank god. what's helped me is consistent exposure to safe people and circumstances, trusting god, therapy, taking risks and loving myself little by little.

who can relate?

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

text:
inilahcom, jakarta - jelang penghujung tahun, instagram melihat kembali momen, konten, dan tren yang terjadi dari seluruh dunia sepanjang tahun ini. "untuk indonesia, 2018 menjadi tahun yang dipenuhi rasa cinta dan bangga, seperti momen kemenangan atlet taekwondo putri defia rosmaniar di asian games dan pengumuman kehamilan penyanyi raisa," kata instagram dalam keterangan resminya.

simbol hati mendominasi konten di instagram sepanjang tahun ini, baik dalam bentuk emoji, gif, dan stiker.

di indonesia dan seluruh dunia, 'heart love by arata' menjadi stiker gif yang paling banyak digunakan oleh pengguna instagram dan "heart eyes" merupakan filter wajah yang paling banyak digunakan di stories.

emoji hati digunakan lebih dari 14 miliar kali di kolom komentar sepanjang tahun 2018.

selain itu, instagram terus menjadi platform yang digunakan pengguna dalam menyebarkan opini dan inspirasi untuk mendatangkan perubahan.

tagar #metoo, #timesup, dan #marchforourlives menjadi tagar dengan pertumbuhan tercepat di instagram secara global, sementara #hspn2018, #welovejakarta, dan #bebassampah2020 menjadi tagar dengan pertumbuhan tercepat di indonesia.

tren komunitas dengan pertumbuhan tercepat di instagram indonesia adalah #bestfanarmy, #ketodiet dan #bisnisanakmuda.

indonesia

#indonesia dan #instagood adalah tagar yang paling banyak digunakan oleh pengguna di indonesia.

stiker gif yang paling banyak digunakan oleh pengguna indonesia di instagram stories: heart love sticker by arata.

text:
¡😱actriz de patito feo acusa al protagonista por violación!
tras la acusación de thelma fardín contra juan darthés por violación, el actor rompió el silencio para presentar su versión de los hechos. "en 2009 estaba de gira en nicaragua con un programa infantil muy exitoso. tenía 16 años, era una nena. el único actor adulto tenía 45 años. una noche comenzó a besarme el cuello. yo le dije que no. me agarró la mano, me hizo que lo tocara y me dijo: ‘mirá cómo me ponés', haciéndome sentir su erección", narró thelma en un estremecedor video presentado esta semana.

continuó entre lágrimas: "yo seguía diciendo que no. me tiró en la cama, me corrió el shortcito. yo seguía diciéndole que no. le dije ‘tus hijos tienen mi edad'. no le importó. se subió encima mío y me penetró". tras estallar el escándalo, había trascendido que juan darthés tuvo que ser internado por un pico de estrés. ahora, el actor de 54 años nacido en brasil ofreció una entrevista. -
con los ojos llorosos y mirando hacia abajo, el actor en el centro del llamado "#metoo argentino" lo negó todo.

juan darthés, de 54 años, salió a desmentir este jueves la acusación de la actriz thelma fardín, de 26 años, quien asegura que la violó en 2009 durante el rodaje de #patitofeo, exitosa serie juvenil argentina.

la denuncia por violación de la actriz thelma fardín contra el actor y cantante juan darthés
darthés dio una entrevista al canal a24 en que calificó de "una locura" la versión hecha pública el martes por fardín.

aunque en la entrevista, con el periodista mauro viale, no quedó claro si hubo un intercambio sexual o no, el actor y cantante aseguró que fue fardín, de 16 años por ese entonces, quien "entró" a su cuarto y se "le insinuó". "ella golpeó la puerta de mi habitación, yo la saqué de mi habitación. '¡estás loca! ¿qué te pasa? soy un tipo grande'", le dije. "mis hijos tenían la misma edad que ella. ¡por dios! ¿cómo puedo hacer una cosa así?", indicó, sobre los detalles que fardín dio.
fuente: @eonlinelatino @bbcmundo #telenovelasrd
name: Novelas

text:
the end says "idk if i'm creating a monster or my own hero"...
unless you have gone through it, i dont think you can begin to fathom what i went through. how i loved a coward who beat and raped me, and then would "honeymoon" me or threaten me with my or his life when that didn't work. 
i'm not sure what's awakening, but i know i'm ready. i know i opened that door. things i'd seemingly forgotten have been flooding my brain. nightmares, that were truly ince my reality. things you'd see on movies, or tv shows. i remember watching maury and seeing the battered women on there being confronted by women who barely lived, and their life being fucked up, thinking "that will never be me....". but it was, it was so hard to accept, but it was.  but see when i flash back to the abuse of him, i begin to hear cries of a child, and flash back from when horrid things happened as a kid come flooding my brain. i went down the path of avoidance through various addictions and denial, what i couldn't get proper help for. 
so when these songs come on, it's more than him or us, it becomes everything, because everything is tied together. all of the things i've stored in my self concious need to be let free, so i can be too. its effecting every relationship i have, and i have had enough. i'm willing to anything to not feel this way anymore. because it hurts so goddamn bad&because i crave more. because i deserve to heal from it all. because wishes do come true. i'm scared of growing cold, i'm scared of the unknown, i'm scared of falling for someone again and having my soul slowly sucked from me. but i'm even more scared of missing out, of being alive yet not living and suffering with regret. it's taking a lot out of me to do this, but being able to make it through and not have a panic attack, let's me know i'm ready. send me love, strength, positivity, patience, empathy, what have you please. 💜 #healing #divorcedlife #divorce
#30anddivorced #domesticviolencerecovery #ptsd #inspire #blogger #blog #motivation #lifetransformation #metoo #survivor #endthesilenceondomesticviolence #stockholmsyndrome #selflove #fighter #enough #rebuildingmylife #positive #domesticviolencesurvivor

text: "the three wise women" flips the conceit of the "the three wise men" who offer gifts to baby jesus.  queen emerald offers the gift of strength via her golden potatoes, queen sapphire offers the gift of wisdom via the yin yang fish, & queen ruby offers hope with her fresh loaf of marzipan stollen.  the trio's journey,  mirrors the trajectory of women over the past several decades. for decades, women have struggled to share their gifts with the world.  the three wise women finally arrive at a place where they can rightfully share their gifts, talent, and compassion with the world.  at this time in our history, women are  blossoming like never before, which is why we placed giant blossom crowns on the heads.  these blossoms are made from discarded bibles which is why artist robert mosley calls them bible blossoms. this is a tribute to the rise of women. #womenrising- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - director @alexcmunoz  actors: @keniarosemary, @msjliu, @queenrubylee  art blossoms designed by @bloomartla.  costumes by @georgiochaplin  music @coldplay  #women #female #queens #metoo #timesup #blacklivesmatter #coldplay #jesus #wise #dtla *we do not own the rights to this music.*

text:
clubs are cool.  unless someone feels like they don’t belong.  i was always chosen last in grade school so i totally get not belonging.  this club though- the self love club?, is better and easier to get into 💕

i spoke to a woman this week who was told that her heart was blocked and if that were true how could she learn to love herself?

first off all- i call bull shit.  the chakras don’t stop moving.  they may slow down but they never stop. 
second of all, self love isn’t about the heart chakra.  selflove starts at the grounding chakra about a foot beneath the earth.  then, as we heal and as we show up for ourselves, set boundaries and keep going it continues to travel up the energy of the body. 
want to know a secret?  there isn’t a cloak we can wear or paleo ourselves into self love.  but we can share and love and ask for help.  and dance.  a lot. 
the only difference between the women who say, “if only i could love myself everything would be okay” and the women who glow with confidence, love and a “fuck if i care” vibe?

healing.  and showing up.  for themselves and other women. 
simple, right?
simple.  not easy. 
i promise though, it happens even for the women who have written off that it would get any better, ever. 
what’s one thing you can do in the next 24 hours?  just one thing.  just for you.  maybe it’s posting, maybe it’s saying no, maybe it’s a yoga class.  just one thing ❤️

text:
eden bourdeau has courageously returned to her pre-dawn runs. a year ago she was violently sexually assaulted after a date and the trauma and ptsd forced her to stop running completely. 
after months of her hard work, she has reclaimed her sport, explaining that running helped her recovery, "i spent months locked inside my house and my own fear. then i went for a run." thank you to @edenboudreau for sharing her story. 
photographed for runner's world

text:
this past year i have had numerous people tell me “you’re strong” or ask “how do you do it?”. at the time i couldn’t help but want to scream “i am not strong, i don’t know what i’m doing!”
.
.
january through to august, my life is a blur. i barely remember people, events and i barely remember life as a whole.
.
.
trauma blocked out half of my year, i’m not sure how, but i survived. from august until now, i am feeling pieces of myself come back. my confidence is coming back, the mom i once was is coming back, the real me is coming back.
.
.
i was broken, i was beat down but i taken these trials and used them as stepping stones.
.
.
i have a long way to go but i am already stronger, i am braver, i am more fierce than i once was. i am being refined.
.
.
#trauma #sexualassault #sexualassaultsurvivor #assault #brave #strong #fierce #livinglife #lovinglife #confident #survivor #warrior #metoo #metoomovement #woman

text:
not original with me.  this is too funny.  credit to ai young. 
since the banning of "baby its cold outside" in light of the #metoo movement, please boycott the christmas song "i want a hippopotamus for christmas" because it exploits endangered hippos.

while we are at it the same goes for:
"santa clause is coming to town" = fake news
"little drummer boy" = gender neutral
"white christmas" = racist and xenophobic
"o' come all ye faithful" = exclusive
"god rest ye merry gentlemen" = anti-feminist
"all i want for christmas is you" = stalking
"blue christmas" = implies male/boy righteousness
"the 12 days of christmas" = anti-semitic (8 days)
"santa baby" = reverse #metoo and exploits handouts
"winter wonderland" = dismisses wonderlands that don't have winter
"its the most wonderful time of the year" = exclusive against 4th of july and summer
"let it snow" = not fair to those where it does not snow
"do you hear what i hear" = insensitive to hearing impaired
"all i want for christmas is my two front teeth" = offensive to meth addicts

and last but not least....
"i saw mommy kissing santa clause” = promotes adultery

text: “it took me several days to build up the courage to do so, but eventually i did.i went to the police. 3,894 days after the attack, 1,825 days since the end of the relationship, and 1,095 days since the memory returned to my conscious mind. in the united states the statue of limitations vary from state to state, crime to crime. where we were when the attack took place has a statute of 20 years. i got lucky. showing up to file my report was one of the most panic inducing things i’ve ever done. i showed up at the local police station and told the officer that i needed to report a nearly 11 year old rape. he was very kind, and encouraged me to stay, but he was honest and up front. after so much time had passed, with out any physical evidence it was really up to the prosecutor to determine if the case would move forward or not.” -r. macceile 2018 candy apple butterscotch: a memoir available now! #fourstars #memoir #metoo #ptsdsurvivor “it’s worth the read it’s about a #woman #empowered and my god that is a #wonderful thing indeed” #linkinbio #authorsofinstagram #independentpublishing #goodreads #newbookalert #readforfree now - dec 25th 100% of proceeds from my books go entirely toward my #holiday #charity #fundraiser benefiting the #afsp you can find more info on rebeccasbookshop.com

text:
marché, marcho y marcharé por nosotras!! "mirá cómo se plantan las mujeres" 20 octubre de 2016
mi relato:
abusaron de mí y de mis amigas también. yo me callé durante muchos años y ellas también. lo olvidé y enterré hasta que un día volvió el recuerdo, y el de ellas también. yo pude salir adelante y mis amigas también. a mí me juzgaron y a ellas también. creí por mucho tiempo haber tenido la culpa, y algunas de ellas también. estuve en un hospital haciéndome análisis y respondiendo preguntas, y algunas de ellas corrieron peor suerte frente a un médico que tuvo que encargarse "del problema".. te duele lo que leés? a nosotras también! y no hablo de mí primera porque soy más víctima, sino para no exponerlas a ellas primero porque muchas aún no pueden hablar, porque soy mujer y las voy a cuidar. pensás que sólo me pasó a mí o a mis amigas? estás equivocadísimx! preguntale con una mano en el corazón a tu hermana, hija, sobrina, tía, mamá o a la primer mujer que te cruces en la calle si no abusaron de ella? si no fue maltratada física y/o verbalmente en una pareja? si un día dijo no e igual hicieron con ella lo que quisieron?!?! y a vos amiga, hablá, contáselo a quien quieras y puedas, pero hablalo xq estos hdp no se merecen el anonimato y estar en las sombras... porque casi todas las mujeres estuvimos en los mismos e incómodos zapatos y porque para construir una nueva sociedad, hay que deconstruir todo lo que está mal!! un día nos dieron trabajo, otro día voz y voto, después nos dieron miedo, pero sabés cuál es la otra cara de eso? la valentía y lucha.. ahora no nos paran, no nos callan, no nos violan ni nos matan más!!! 💪 aylen
#niunamenos #miracomonosponemos #sevaacaer #girlpower #notenemosmiedo #lucha #nonoscallanmas #yo #metoo #abajoelpatriarcado #mujeres #launionhacelafuerza #habla #denuncia #noesno
name: Aylen Benedetti Varela

text:
يمتلك الواقع الافتراضي الكثير من الإمكانيات التي باستطاعتها توعية النساء اللواتي يعشن تحت سقف واحد مع الزوج المُعنِّف، خاصة وأن معظمهن لا يدركن سوى العنف الجسدي دون دراية بحجم الخسائر التي يسببها العنف المعنوي، و التهديد، و التخويف و العنف الجنسي. لذلك فمن الضروري أن يسترشدن من أجل الحصول على الدعم الذي يحتجنه من أجل توفير الأمان والانعتاق من الوسط العنيف الذي يعشن فيه. ‎كيف يمكن لامرأة أمية بشكل خاص تواجه العنف المنزلي أن تفهم نوع العنف الذي تواجهه وماذا تفعل لضمان سلامتها؟
‎من جهة أخرى تحتاج الجمعيات التي توفر خدمات الاستماع والاستشارة القانونية والنفسية للنساء اللواتي يتعرضن للاعتداء بهذه الطريقة إلى هذا الحل لتكون قادرة على توفير الدعم المناسب والضروري لهن جميعا خلال زياراتهن كل أسبوع؛ السبب في استعمال الواقع الافتراضي في مرحلة التشخيص والإبلاغ لأفضل الممارسات يمكن أن يكون لها تأثير كبير وإيجابي. 
#ماتضربنيش

text:
tw: ipv, self harm
when isabella mosqueda was a freshman in high school, she was struggling with mental health issues and had a hard time opening up. a friend introduced her to rachel*, a senior at their school who was going through similar challenges. their friendship blossomed quickly. “honestly it was super refreshing. i had only been in small, conservative, private schools and never felt like i could talk to someone about my mental health issues or the abusive household i grew up in,” remembers isabella. “for a while, it was kind of magical.” they started dating three months later.
what began as a balanced relationship soon grew controlling. “it’s hard to say when the abuse started,” said isabella. “when we were first dating, it was like a disney story: we’d talk 24/7; she wrote me a love song; we danced in the snow. then things started changing, subtly at first.” rachel became adamant about knowing isabella’s whereabouts and would call her incessantly. she also tried to control what clothes isabella wore. eventually rachel convinced isabella to abandon her other friends and family. “i felt crappy sometimes, but convinced myself it was because she cared about me and she wanted to keep me safe." it’s taken isabella many years to come to terms with the physical coercion that also existed in the relationship. “the first time we kissed was the first day we started going out. i was not ready, but she told me we needed to make our relationship official.” the abuse eventually escalated. “when i told her i wasn’t ready [to have sex] she asked me, “well don’t you love me?” i said, “yes of course,” but she wanted me to prove it.” for the next four months, rachel continued to coerce isabella into sexual acts. “after it happened the first time, and every time after that, i’d take a shower and scrub myself clean. then i would cut myself and try to get her out of me."

text: 2018 was a year full of growth and laughter for all the right and wrong reasons. between making an encore appearance in cancun, to the breakout of fortnite, to realizing just how tough “adulting” can be. this year was full of characters (both real and fake) . i learned how to make risotto better than ramsey. my daily routine consisted of binge watching masterclass and i started day trading on robinhood with the help of the great ross cameron. thanos has shown his face, and dutch shown his true colors. at 25, i’ve learned a lot and had a lot of fun along the way so far. swipe thru to see my highlights this year.

text:
el lado oscuro >> juan darthés dibuja una jugada de manual: se victimiza y revierte la carga de la responsabilidad: "ya estoy muerto" dice. el actor apela a su naturaleza y se muestra  vulnerable (lo intenta). pero es imposible ver al doctor jekyll. es el señor hyde quien copa la escena. a diferencia de la novela del británico stevenson del siglo xix, aquí no hay una pócima que expone la dimensión misántropa de un hombre. se trata simplemente de un tipo abrumado por la coyuntura: lo que durante muchos años permaneció oculto, tolerado o incluso sostenido por la superestructura patriarcal de la industria cultural, hoy sale a la luz en forma de liberación, de justicia y revolución.

text:
anti-violence group member accused of sexual assault-
fox news & cbs news reports...
serious allegations against the bosses of a well-known anti-violence group.
several women said they were sexually assaulted and harassed. one state lawmaker is now deciding whether to continue her support of the group cure violence formerly called ceasefire.
cbs news chicago interview- in february of 2017 angalia bianca worked dangerous streets trying to prevent violence. “i’m never afraid,” bianca said adding that she relished the work for the group ceasefire. “i’ve completely 100 percent dedicated my life to the inner-city streets.”
but inside the ceasefire offices, bianca said her life was made miserable by a supervisor. “cobe williams sexually assaulted me in the workplace on several occasions,” bianca said.cobe is ricardo “cobe” williams, a senior administrator at ceasefire, which is now called cure violence.
“following his sexual advances cobe began to harass me because i did not comply,” she said.
bianca has filed a federal lawsuit against williams, his boss, the creator of the program, gary slutkin and the university of illinois at chicago. cure violence is part of the uic school of public health. #metoo #unacceptable

text:
"amurallar el propio sufrimiento es arriesgarte a que te devore desde el interior". #fridakahlo (pintora mexicana, 1907-1954). los casos de denuncias por acoso y violación contra actores, locutores y periodistas argentinos en el ámbito de la radio y televisión me recordaron al "me too" y en especial al  calvario que sufrió salma hayek con un productor para poder filmar la película frida:
"[...]como mujeres, nos han devaluado artísticamente como si fuéramos indecentes a tal punto que la industria fílmica dejó de esforzarse en averiguar lo que quieren ver las audiencias femeniles y las historias que queremos contar.
de acuerdo con un estudio reciente, entre 2007 y 2016 solo cuatro por ciento de los directores fueron mujeres y 80 por ciento de ellas pudieron hacer solamente una película. en 2016, según otro estudio, solo el 27 por ciento de los diálogos en las principales películas fueron dichos por mujeres. y la gente se pregunta por qué no dijimos nada antes. creo que las estadísticas se explican por sí mismas: nuestras voces no son bienvenidas.
hasta que haya igualdad en la industria, que los hombres y mujeres tengan la misma valía en todos los aspectos de la producción, nuestra comunidad seguirá siendo tierra fértil para los depredadores.
estoy agradecida con todos los que están escuchando nuestras experiencias. espero que al agregar mi voz al coro de quienes por fin pudieron hablar ayudaré a entender por qué fue tan difícil hacerlo y por qué tantas de nosotras esperamos tanto tiempo. los hombres acosan sexualmente porque pueden. y las mujeres estamos hablando porque, en esta nueva era, por fin podemos hacerlo."
[párrafo extraído de 👉https://www.nytimes.com/es/2017/12/13/salma-hayek-harvey-weinstein/ .] 🔘 #miracomonosponemos #noesno #metoo  #pinturadigital #digitalpaint #instapaint  #digitalillustration #artgram #fineart #digitalart #digitalartwork #instaart  #instaartwork  #digitalsketch 🔘

text_retweet:
🔥 saiu o instagram's top trends de 2018 💜
ㅤ
com 2018 quase chegando ao fim, o instagram do facebook destacou algumas tendências do ano e compartilhou todas as maneiras pelas quais a comunidade do instagram usou a plataforma para se expressar.
ㅤ
de acordo com o instagram, compartilhar amor e bondade ainda é uma prioridade para a comunidade no instagram: o heart love sticker de arata foi o adesivo do giphy mais usado em stories, enquanto heart eyes foi o filtro de rosto mais usado em stories. em feed, o emoji ❤ "coração" foi usado em comentários mais de 14 bilhões de vezes. o lugar mais feliz do mundo? disneyland tokyo, que também teve o maior uso do emoji 🙂 "sorriso" no texto da legenda.
ㅤ
o instagram é o lugar de inúmeros interesses e comunidades; este ano, a asmr foi a principal tendência da comunidade de nichos do ano, continuando a aumentar a sua popularidade.
ㅤ
o jogo fortnite também teve um crescimento explosivo, com a #fortnite sendo a hashtag que mais cresce no mundo. o domínio do k-pop nas mídias sociais é refletido pelo bts “army” sendo a principal comunidade de fãs na plataforma.
ㅤ
o maior desafio de dança viral do ano também nasceu no instagram, com #inmyfeelingschallenge, que incluiu todos, de @theshiggyshow a @willsmith, chegando ao número 1.

por último, mas não menos importante, milhões de pessoas usaram o instagram para fazer suas vozes serem ouvidas em 2018. as principais hashtags do ano foram #metoo (1,5 milhão), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k).
ㅤ
ㅤ
resumo de 2018 no instagram:
ㅤ
● filtro de rosto mais usado em histórias no instagram: heart eyes
● gif do giphy mais usado nas histórias no instagram: heart love sticker by arata
● número de vezes que o emoji ❤ "coração" foi usado nos comentários: 14 bilhões
● o lugar mais feliz do mundo (e com maior uso do emoji 🙂 "sorriso" na legenda): disneyland tokyo
● tendência da comunidade de nicho: asmr
● hashtag com maior crescimento: #fortnite
● comunidade fandom: bts (#btsarmy)
● top dance movement: #inmyfeelingschallenge
● principais hashtags usadas por uma causa: #metoo (1,5 milhões), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k)
ㅤ
ㅤ
e você o que achou do ano de 2018?
#repost @ricardocelso

el #miracomonosponemos en números:
- en 2 días generó 1,3 millones de tweets relacionados.
- 1240% crecieron las denuncias al 114 por abuso infantil.
- 18.892 retweets y 37.259 favs y 2.300 comentarios de apoyo y agradecimiento tuvo el tweet de thelma. - los 3 hasgtags relacionados más usados en la conversación fueron: #nonoscallamosmás, #metoo y #sevaacaer. (fuente: twitter)
- "no es no" fue el término asociado más buscado en internet. (fuente google trends) - $690 por unidad es lo que quiso cobrar una marca de moda en la pre-venta de una remera con el lema de la lucha contra. que luego puso en liquidación a $518.
- menos de 24 horas duró la remera a la venta y la marca tuvo que salir a pedir disculpas.
- 1 sólo es el desafío para las marcas: no aprovecharse de las situaciones, sino acompañar el movimiento de un modo auténtico y donde el lucro no esté asociado. 
ninguna marca puede salir a vender pañuelos ni apropiarse de este movimiento que recién empieza y ya se vislumbra que generará grandes cambios sociales, entre ellos repensar el rol que deben tener las marcas en todo esto.

text:
this is one of the biggest mistakes people are making when it comes to personal development ⬇️
.
they try to bottle it up or push things aside instead of doing the work!
.
it’s so easy to be intimidated, scared, or put off by facing your struggles and trauma head on, but unless you deal with it it’s going to continue to affect you!
.
i’ve seen so many people (myself included) who hope things will magically fix themselves. they try to ignore the pain, sadness or anger and continue to keep busy with other aspects of life.
.
they mask the negative emotions/experiences with partying, drinking, diving headfirst into relationships or staying consumed by work.
.
but the thing is... if you’re doing that then you still haven’t fixed the problem! you’re just trying to keep yourself so busy that you don’t have time to face it in hopes that it will disappear!
.
pain doesn’t disappear. hardships don’t disappear. trauma, grief, anxiety, and old struggles from your childhood don’t disappear!!! 🙅🏼‍♀️
.
they are just sitting under the surface waiting for any and every chance to return. they return in patterns that will drive you crazy, in emotional breakdowns, or in random outbursts of anger that don’t fit the scenario.
.
so it’s literally up to you whether you want to work through them and find a release once and for all.... or if you want to continue to try and win a race that you can never win. 🏃🏼‍♀️
.
because i promise you - that negativity will catch up with you someday and pop up in ways you never imagined.
.
so tell me this: are you ready to release the baggage and negative energy that’s secretly draining you? or are you content to keep going the way that things are? 🤔
.
the choice is yours. 🙏🏼

text:
sleep can be terrifying. for most of my life, as far back as i can remember, i’ve suffered from night terrors. they come and go, sometimes they can even disappear for months, and then they return, often bigger and more terrifying. .
.
it all stems from a very traumatic incident in my childhood, which is so deeply preserved within my subconscious. i can manage the haunting memories, more or less, when i’m awake (only the odd panic attack or bouts of anxiety) but it’s during times of vulnerability (stress, fatigue, illness) while i’m asleep, when my guard is down, that these terrors rise up in the depths of the night and take an unexpected and horrifying hold on me.
.
.
i’ve had two nights of terror this week and i’m dreading tonight. .
.
i wanted to share this as i know i’m not the only one out there who suffers from this curse. my heart goes out to you. .
.
just remember to come back to your deep slow exhales when you are jolted out of your sleep by a petrifying dream. i also like to recite the alphabet to help distract and refocus my mind. sounds silly but it works. you’d do anything to erase the fear from your mind - and somehow i’ve found this really helps me. .
.
and so i bid you lala salama 💖💖
.
.
.

text:
have you been following cyntoia brown’s story? at 16, she was forced into prostitution. she was a child. even if she was a “willing” participant (which cyntoia argues; she was forced), she is still a survivor. her story has similarities to every other story of rape and sexual violence. she was hurt, and people with authority not only did not believe her, but they criminalized her immediately, which is what happens to other survivors who come forward to tell their stories. dr. ford is a great and recent example of how our society immediately demonizes survivors.
we are not a judge, nor are we a jury. we are supporters. at rcccnm, we believe cyntoia brown just like we believe any survivor who tells us they have experienced sexual violence. cyntoia’s story gives us a grim look into the way this country still views survivors, especially survivors who are also people of color. has anyone thought about the implications of labeling children (who are trafficked, prostituted, or involved in survival sex work) as criminals - for crimes that were committed against them? what happens when that label follows them for the rest of their lives?
well, what happens is these children, who are no stranger to oppression, will be tossed back into the cycle. these child survivors will have to hear at such a young age that they are not believed and that the deserve their circumstances.
at rcccm, we believe survivors. we believe that for sexual violence to end, all forms of oppression must end. cyntoia brown’s story is a perfect example of this.
#cyntoiabrown #endoppression ndrapeculture #sexualassaultawareness #believesurvivors #webelieveyou #endsexualviolence #metoo

text:
como le toques un pelo, te arranco la mano. como tengas un solo pensamiento injurioso, me encargo de que no vuelvas a usar eso que tienes encima de los hombros de la misma manera, y que sirva para algo más que para peinarte, porque si vas a abusar, me va a dar igual si lo haces guapo o feo porque te mirare con los mismos ojos de asco, decepción y aborrecimiento.  lo que le haces a ella, me lo haces a mi. así que cuidado, porque igual que tú te juntas con tus amigos para buscar víctimas para vuestras gamberradas, nosotras nos apoyamos cuando las hacéis. no siempre funciona, es verdad, pero date cuenta de que la revolución está aquí. porque lo que me haces a mi, hoy también se lo haces a ella. a ellas. ahora es en plural.
mira como nos ponemos.
#licor43ynata
.
.
.#miracomonosponemos #quotes #textos #frases #women #feminismo #noesno #women #stronhwomen #metoo

text:
serena williams is breaking down barriers left and right. 
the star tennis player made history on wednesday as the first woman to ever wear cornrows on a teen vogue cover. williams looks serene and powerful on the magazine’s december cover issue, sporting a coral jacket and delicate gold earrings. 
williams explained in the interview why it’s so important to support women, but especially her fellow women of color. “we really have to support each other,” she said. “i always like to say that women really should support each other, because the success of one woman should be the inspiration to the next. if we look at it that way, there would be so much more that we can accomplish.” the cover was shot by another black woman, british photographer ronan mckenzie.

text:
desde mcv colectivo artístico, las mujeres adherimos al comunicado de la colectiva de actrices argentinas del martes 11 de diciembre de 2018.
las actrices y trabajadoras de la industria del arte y el entretenimiento somos ignoradas al denunciar y exponer los abusos. se duda sistemáticamente de nuestras voces y de nuestros testimonios. en nuestro medio, la opresión y cosificación son moneda corriente. estamos casi siempre desprotegidas por quienes nos contratan. no hay protocolos de acción frente a casos de abuso; y la lista podría seguir porque es inmensa.
necesitamos herramientas para enfrentar estas cuestiones que además se ven agudizadas por la precariedad laboral y la falta de trabajo. algunos medios intentan llevar la atención hacia el costado más morboso de los conflictos, mientras acallan las problemáticas de fondo. contra todas esas formas de violencia y para que esto cambie, nos ponemos a trabajar desde hoy, desde ya para dar esa batalla.
donde la justicia y el estado obstaculizan, desestiman, demoran, estigmatizan a las víctimas o fallan en forma aberrante a favor de los victimarios, nos convocamos para decir basta. porque el tiempo del silencio y de la impunidad para los abusadores se terminó.
los abusadores tienen el privilegio de utilizar el sistema de justicia para disciplinarnos. mientras, las víctimas sufren las prescripciones, dilaciones, malos tratos y descreimiento por parte del aparato judicial. frente a este maltrato, esta indiferencia y mordaza legal, las actrices nos organizamos.
frente al “mirá cómo me ponés”, nosotras decimos “mirá cómo nos ponemos”

#miracomonosponemos 💪🔥
#noesno !!
#secae 🔥
#sisterhood #stillirise #metoo

text:
en brasil se ha presentado una polémica con un gran movimiento debido a que casi 500 mujeres han acusado de abuso sexual, a juan de dios, quien es un guía espiritual, el lema de este caso es #metoo (yo también brasileño). las mujeres pronuncian que la técnica que usaba el supuesto médium era que con su “cirugía sin corte” lograría curar sus enfermedades, de la depresión a un cáncer.

estas acusaciones existen desde el año 2010, aun que el tema salió a la luz con mayor intensidad debido a que tv globo y el diario o globo reportaron varios casos parecidos de mujeres que acusan al sanador, incluso una coreógrafa holandesa zahira quien asegura ser victima de este señor, de 76 años. “joão fue perseguido y acusado por práctica ilegal de la medicina. en el período de la dictadura militar, fue a brasilia a trabajar como sastre para el ejército. allí, ejerció trabajos de sanación y ganó la protección de los militares”, afirma la biografía de joão de deus.

y aún así se presenta que “cerca de 9 millones de personas, según su propia contabilidad, ya se desplazaron hasta el interior de goiás para someterse a sus cirugías espirituales”, informa ese medio.
name: Periódico Amarillo

y aún así se presenta que “cerca de 9 millones de personas, según su propia contabilidad, ya se desplazaron hasta el interior de goiás para someterse a sus cirugías espirituales”, informa ese medio.

text: the amount of times i’ve had to pull men’s hands away from my cunt, push people off who have tried to pin me down and suck my tits or fight with people who have decided it is their right to touch me even after i’ve said no is unbelievable. since my most recent sexual assault a part of me has changed. part of me shut down at first - i couldn’t look at men without thinking i was unsafe and constantly felt on edge. i felt shame for what had happened to me - in fact i still have days where i feel like what happened to me is my fault. however, the most recent attack has been different in terms of my response. this time i was surrounded by remarkable people who gave me the confidence and support to speak up and get justice for what happened to me. so to men and women who have been victims of sexual assault i implore you you to use your voice. no matter where you are in the world, whether you’re in a different culture .. consent for you should always mean the same thing 👊🏻you have the power to speak up and be heard when a perpetrator does everything to silence you & try and control you. it’s not your fault if this happens to you. no one has the right to touch you if you don’t want to be touched. i post nude photos on instagram and i am very sexual liberated but that does not decrease my value & worth. i’m not “asking for it” but you are definitely going to get it if you cross me or anyone else who you don’t have permission to touch 👋🏻👋🏻👋🏻👋🏻👋🏻👋🏻 i will post more about this topic on my blog in the future. thanks for reading ✍🏻 #sexualassault #metoo

text:
thursday at parlor with the wonderful and talented elizabeth waggett @_waggs “she pulled a pistol from her knickers (now) and (then)”, 22 karat gold, champagne gold, ink, charcoal and graphite on cotton, 22x16”, (framed), and yes it is a drawing..
•
“she pulled a pistol from her knickers”. this is a line taken from the great, roald dahl’s ‘revolting rhymes’ book and chosen to emphasize the power of the response from the women who are standing up and taking part in the ‘me too’ campaign, a power that has come from abuse. using a gun to symbolize the power of the campaign, also actively explores the subject of guns and gun culture. the pieces are intended to excite thought and conversation, both startling and challenging. by the artist in her own words...
•
we are always happy to show thought provoking works that engage the viewer. for more information about elizabeth and her available works, email us at info@parlor-gallery.com or dm for pricing and details.

text:
@silkmentoring is happy to share  tarana burke and alyssa milan as the faces for empathy exemplified.

tarana burke social activist and community organizer, began using the phrase "me too" in 2006, on the myspace social network as part of a campaign to promote "empowerment through empathy" among women of color who have experienced sexual abuse, particularly within underprivileged communities. burke, who is creating a documentary titled me too, has said she was inspired to use the phrase after being unable to respond to a 13-year-old girl who confided to her that she had been sexually assaulted. burke later wished she had simply told the girl, "me too". alyssa milano encouraged spreading the hashtag #metoo, to attempt to draw attention to sexual assault and harassment. milano later acknowledged earlier use of the phrase by burke.

credit to:
https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/me_too_movement

text:
needed a reminder today, of why i do what i love and what purpose it all has for me. i dedicate my passion, my life and my self to helping, entertaining, supporting, uplifting and embracing others. art is only one form in which i try to fight for equality.
donate, petition, converse, protest, march, learn, educate....only when we allow ourselves to be truly awake and face the masses can we then fight for what we believe in. i am so thankful for these women as well as the many other mujeres that fight along side with me everyday. from self care talks, to actually marching through the streets of la, to those i’ve traveled with all over the world to share the message, to those i’ve cried to and with. with out you i truly do not know where i would be. with the end of the year amongst us, i keep reflecting the same question over and over again....yes it can be a bit stressful but it also keeps the fire alive:
have you done enough while keeping your soul alive and in tact? 📷 miss @alexandrameda 
btw want some strong ass women to help you breathe and ignite your fire? come see #thetimes with us @teatroluna ❤️ link in bio✌🏾

text:
“one of the songs i’m about to record, i wrote during the #metoo movement. it’s about assault, basically. it’s called, “i owe you nothing.” i wrote that around that time, and i couldn’t get, like, how i wanted the vibe of the song. i had the lyrics and everything finished, but i couldn’t get the vibe right, and we finally got it. it took a while. because it’s an important message… it’s not even a story, but it’s from my experiences, and i want someone else to hear that, and not only think that it sounds good, but be, like, “hell yeah.” i don’t know, i definitely could. i could see myself writing more, at least female-driven music. a lot of the songs from my first record are definitely female-oriented.” - emily nenni

text:
make friends with uncomfortable emotions and thoughts,  until perhaps you charm them into kinder versions of themselves. where you can gently “curl up with a cup of tea”. soon there will be only rings left on the table and perhaps a sweet spill of honey. but if you lock them away they are sure to feed on the darkness. in the light they fear their own shadows and seek new refuge. 
#thisisit #metoo #brave #warriors #karaleeyoga #notgenderspecific #courage #speakupspeakout #

text:
if a grown man had done what the peer did to my child he would be in jail.

if a teenager had done what the peer did to my child, he would be expelled and charged.

a peer the same age as my son, sexually assaults my child and it is swept under the rug. my child has to look at this boy every. single. day. 
he wasnt punished. he wasnt even suspended. i pulled my kid out of school for 22 days and that kid got to enjoy his education while my child sat at home wondering why no one was helping him. 
now, that kid is trying to play victim. he wants my son to get in trouble for telling his story because he is embarrassed about what he did. the principal is standing behind him because he was "going through alot at the time"... my child is a victim and we had to fight to get him support. we had to change his classroom so he wouldnt have to look at that child all day, every day because that childs dad didnt want his class switched. since when is sexual assault condoned in the catholic church? at six years old! since when does society think that this is ok?? that child needs help, more so than my child does.. and so does the other victim. what happened to my kid isn't a "normal" sexual act. it was something that kid had to have witnessed or experienced himself. 
please help us find the other victim. the catholic school board would have no choice but to help all 3 children if we found her!! the other victim is likely in the east end of peterborough.

#shatterthesilence #metoo #ptbocanada #ptbo #peterboroughontario #peterborough #kawarthalakes #sexualassault #endthestigma #mentalhealth #catholic #kids #canada #standupfortheoneswithoutavoice

text:
har du nogensinde tænkt om et produkt at det ikke kunne være så godt som sælgeren sagde? det har jeg…
.
i lang tid var det sådan jeg tænkte om @doterra, fordi - let’s face it - det er bare essentielle olier og dem er der masser af på markedet. og hvad skal jeg egentlig med dem?
. 
da jeg startede med at behandle søgte jeg også lidt rundt på nettet efter hvad de forskellige olier kan og brugte mine faste to: tea tree oil og eucalyptus. de gav en god og frisk duft plus de var ifølge google gode til at berolige de mennesker, der skulle ligge på min briks.
. 
doterra dukkede ofte op i mit ig feed og til diverse workshops jeg deltog i, og selvom jeg synes de var lækre, så tænkte jeg ikke så meget over det...
så startede jeg på @livingyolatesacademy immersion rejse! mikkala bruger olierne i diffuseren hver gang vi træner! og hvilken himmelsk forskel!! min træning derhjemme var ikke lige så fokuseret og powerful som når jeg var på uddannelse (bevares, 20 smukke sjæle til at dele turen med har absolut meget at gøre med det!) og jeg har nu opdaget hvorfor!
. 
jeg selv investeret i olierne nu og kan afgjort sige at de gør en daglig forskel for mit fokus, mit humør og min (og min families) søvn - bare for at nævne lidt! det er blevet meget nemmere at komme i gang med de ting jeg skal nå og selv hvis det blot er placebo - så er det i hvert fald effektivt!!
og doterra gør det virkelig nemt at lære at bruge olierne til alle mulige hverdagsting. jeg glæder mig i hvert fald enormt meget til at lære endnu mere og bruge rene produkter til alt fra rengøring til menstruationssmerter.
. 
så jeg må sande at jeg har ændret min mening om hvorvidt et produkt virkelig kan være så godt som sælgeren siger… for doterra er bare bedre!
. 
hvis du vil høre mere, så send mig en besked!
. 
tak for at læse med 💜
.
.
.
#verdenifølgemaria #taknemmeligtype #doterra #essentielleolier #hurra #winningatlife

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates suppoed by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
hoy quiero contarles a grandes rasgos lo que he pasado estos días, todo con el fin de exponer un testimonio, visibilizar la triste realidad de los músicos frente a la noche y darle fuerza a l@s que estén pasando por algo similar. el lunes 10 de diciembre, aproximadamente a las 2am, tras un show privado en el que estuve cantando para una compañía internacional de artistas, un hombre ruso, perteneciente a ella, llamado nikolai ermolae, aparentemente muy amable y respetuoso , con el que entablé conversación amistosa como se hace con el público que aplaude la música que se ofrece con total entusiasmo, en un momento totalmente inesperado, me abordó, siendo extremadamente violento. la primera vez logré escapar  sin mucho éxito, él logró arrastrarme a la fuerza nuevamente mientras yo forcejeaba y me agarraba de las puertas y paredes gritando para que alguien me ayudara. en esta ocasión fue aún más violento que la primera vez (no contaré detalles). logré forcejear con todas mis fuerzas para poder escapar y así librarme de algo peor. 
decidí demandarlo ante la fiscalía por abuso sexual. la compañía para la cual él trabaja y su crew me han apoyado y tras investigar, lo han sacado de ella. la justicia está primando, lo cual me da tranquilidad. talvez algunos dirán por ahí “se lo buscó, fue muy ingenua, dio papaya”, y tal vez si fui muy confiada, pero absolutamente nada excusa el hecho de que alguien invada tu espacio personal y te lastime y agreda de tal manera. mi llamado es a que por favor todos cuidemos de todos, a que ustedes siendo público en un show, cuiden a sus músicos y no traicionen ese voto de confianza: que los borrachos no se vuelvan manilargos, que el piropo no se transforme en insinuación grosera y atrevida, que la invitación no termine en abuso y violencia. todo lo que hacemos lo hacemos por la pasión y amor a la música, a ustedes, a hacer de este mundo uno menos feo, apoyémonos y no pasemos esos límites nunca, para generar (para todos) un espacio tanto de entretenimiento, como de trabajo, sanos, seguros y estables. (continúa abajo 👇🏽) #metoo #laramona #cerotoleranciaalmaltrato

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
day 13. exploitation in all forms is wrong. trafficking is wrong, rape is wrong, attempted rape is wrong, molestation is wrong, harassment is wrong, all forms of physical/sexual intimidation is wrong. exerting power over another for your own pleasure or profit is unequivocally wrong and evil. .
.
sadly, today’s headlines don’t always tell the same story: rapists receive a slap in the wrist and often the abused is criminalized or marginalized for speaking up or acting out in self defense.
.
.
i believe change is possible— that we can and are moving toward a less misogynistic world, a less racist/colorist world, toward one where people are valued and treated and dignified and believed as human beings, and those who’d perpetuate unhealthy systemic abuses of power will be the ones silenced and made to feel ashamed.
.
.
 @aminatou says that “no man is a full time rapist.” a man who would rape is probably living a normal life, has friends and coworkers and even a wife/girlfriend. most people perceive him as “a good guy”. but when the thread of misogyny is deep and long standing and both subtle and obvious in our culture and other cultures, violence against women is inevitable. to end trafficking, we must uproot and end misogyny.
.
.
but how do we get there? talking about it. acknowledging these fundamental imbalances and abuses of power. dressember is a chance to speak up; to use a deceptively nonthreatening vehicle like fashion to take part in changing the dialogue around sex and power. we’re in this together, and we’re a force to be reckoned with. #itsbiggerthanadress #untilallarefree #dressember #metoo #metoomovement #potteragreesbutwasntfeelingthepic

text:
una debe ser fiel a sus convicciones y no lo digo como mujer sino como persona. no es casual que el feminismo se asocie a algo malo y éste ligado a tantos estereotipos negativos (y por supuesto errados) es lo que el patriarcado quiere, nunca te lo pusiste a pensar?
 hemos llegado al punto de que minas tengan que salir a decir "no soy feminista pero"... dejame decirte que el simple hecho de ser consciente de que hay desigualdad entre hombres y mujeres en cualquier aspecto posible, el simple hecho de advertirlo ya te hace feminista en un punto, no tenés que sentir vergüenza por querer que tus derechos no sean vulnerados, luego por supuesto queda todo un camino realmente difícil y penoso de andar, donde se hace un mea culpa y te percatás que fueron machistas con vos muchos años y lo veías como normal o peor aún que te lo guardadas porque sabías bien que sí lo decías serias cuestionada, ignorada... capaz que hasta fuiste machista vos también o te quedabas callada cuando veías que lo  eran con otras. ser feminista es enfrentar el hecho de que todo lo que te pareció "normal" desde que naciste tiene que ser deconstruido y cuesta mucho. pero una vez que te sacás las vendas de los ojos (y atravesás esa metamorfosis interna) viene lo mejor que es tomar fuerzas para cambiar éste mundo podrido que nos tocó para nacer, y quizá con cierta melancolía sepas que no llegues a ver el mundo que anhelaste pero que contribuiste para dejar un mundo un poquito menos horrendo para todas las que nacerán después.

this leaf is my leaf. ✨🌱 the first survivor leaf entry i wrote one night when i couldn’t sleep. all three of my stories are written here. i’m proud of this leaf. while each of these experiences was born in pain, i have come so far since these darknesses in my life. i’ve pushed through fear, anxiety, shame, guilt- and i’m still here. gone are shame and guilt (i’m still working on fear and anxiety, and that’s okay. work is progress!), and i’ve finally found a way to come back into the light. survivorship is something that never goes away- i’ll never be able to erase these memories.  but i have transformed their power over me. i painted, i wrote, i created, and i grew them into something beautiful. i was recently speaking to a friend and fellow survivor and told her that, while there have been times in my past that i have felt empowered *in spite of* being a survivor, i have never felt empowered *because* i am a survivor- until now. this work is changing me. ✨🌱 click the link in my bio to contribute your story to the survivor tree. #rapesurvivor #survivor #survivoradvocate #survivorselfcare #metoo #whyididntreport #drchristineblaseyford #endrapeculture #believewomen #believesurvivors #believeblackwomen #timesup #artist #wip #workinprogress #

text:
in an interview with 'the new york times,' fox opened up about being "victim shamed" regarding #metoo stories in the past. 
almost ten years ago, fox spoke publicly about her experiences with director michael bay on two 'transformers' movies. fox said he commanded her to "just be sexy" and "be hot" on set. fox was also sexualized in bay's 2003 film 'bad boys ii,' where she danced under a waterfall in a bikini and high heels. fox was only 15 years old at the time and said, "i just did what i was told to do." the actress was ultimately fired from the 'transformers' franchise for her remarks. 
#trendbahn #trendbahnnews #metoo #meganfox

text:
new concentration piece!
i’ve been told by multiple people(not just guys) that women are better liked with no makeup. i think it’s perfectly fine to not wear it, and it’s fine to wear it. some days i like to put on a full face, other days it’s just bare face. it really shouldn’t matter either way, everyone is entitled to their own way of personal expression. because i like to wear makeup, it shouldn’t make me less desirable or fake. i don’t wear it because i’m self conscious or trying to deceive/ impress people. i wear it because to me, makeup is just another form of art. ❤️💄 —————————-

i’ve been told by multiple people(not just guys) that women are better liked with no makeup. i think it’s perfectly fine to not wear it, and it’s fine to wear it. some days i like to put on a full face, other days it’s just bare face. it really shouldn’t matter either way, everyone is entitled to their own way of personal expression. because i like to wear makeup, it shouldn’t make me less desirable or fake. i don’t wear it because i’m self conscious or trying to deceive/ impress people. i wear it because to me, makeup is just another form of art. ❤️💄 —————————-

text:
“in memory of her”
...
i made this clay sculpture for the @gardinermuseum and @schliferclinic’s expressive arts group for women who have experienced violence. my piece is a big pomegranate with a broken wall and a tiny, perfect pomegranate. it represents me and my journey to healing through art. i was sexually assaulted while studying abroad in jerusalem—my friend came into my bedroom at night and raped me. the clay invited me to explore my trauma and challenged me to trust the art-making process. my piece shares my brokenness and reflects my experience of falling apart, splitting into discordant fragments, and losing a central part of my identity.

detta kontot finns kvar men jag har valt att lämna de sociala medierna på obestämd tid. just för att försöka dämpa stressen, ångesten och alla faktorer som trycker ner mig. jag kommer fortsätta på denna sidan senare både för min egna skull och även i hopp om att kunna hjälpa andra. psykisk ohälsa syns inte på utsidan men den finns i varje del och varje minut av en drabbads liv. psykisk ohälsa drabbar vem som helst och det kan skada mer än vissa ens kan förstå. psykisk ohälsa lever än i dag i det tysta och den enda önskan som finns är att göra psykiska ohälsa till ett större ämne för omvärlden och att psykisk ohälsa ska bli ett större ämne inom vården, mer hjälp och mer resurser. ja ni vet allt. tack för ert stöd och tills vi hörs nästa gång. ta hand om varandra ni är bäst. ♥️🙏🏻

text_retweet:
#repost @carlaw443 with @get_repost
・・・
(reuters) - attorneys for bill cosby outlined their grounds on tuesday for appealing his sexual assault conviction, citing what they called errors in legal procedure that may have biased the jury and warrant a new trial for the once-beloved comedian. the 81-year-old performer, best known for his role as the lovable family man and physician on the hit television sitcom “the cosby show,” was found guilty by a pennsylvania jury in april of drugging and sexually assaulting a onetime friend in 2004.

it marked the first such criminal conviction of a celebrity accused of sexual misconduct since the #metoo movement that has brought down dozens of powerful, privileged men in american media, politics and business since the autumn of 2017.

in september, the trial judge, steven o’neill, designated cosby a “sexually violent predator” under pennsylvania law, requiring the entertainer to register as a sex offender for life, and sentenced him to a term of three to 10 years in prison.

cosby, who is married, has insisted all along that any sexual encounters he had were consensual. he was found guilty on three counts of aggravated indecent assault.

in an eight-page filing laying out the basis of their appeal, cosby’s lawyers focused on several instances they said introduced bias into the trial, including the judge’s refusal to excuse a juror that the defense argued was unable to be fair and impartial. #freebillcosby #farfromfinished #justice #corruption #thecosbyshow #blackexcellence #wronglyconvicted #billcosby

text:
some of you are new here, welcome! i wanna let you in on a little secret. my name is alyssa, i am a mom of 3 amazing little boys, and i struggle with depression. i have for most of my life. in the last few years though it has gotten to the point that i didn't see the point of me being here anymore. my boys would be better off not watching their mom struggle. 
_
first this isn't true. they need me. more than i realize some days. second, i did the hardest thing i could. i talked about it. i was honest. it broke me admitting that i felt i wasn't the mom my boys need. in reaching out though, i was able to get help. am i perfect? no, not even close. i still have my days. they are far less than they year to be and i can thank essential oils for that. by supporting my body on a cellular level, i feel happy again. happier than i can ever remember being, since i was at least 9 years old... i have stress away, joy and lavender essential oils to thank for bringing me back. 
_
you aren't alone, you can find peace and i can help you get on the right path. essential oils are so easy to use, this newbie figured it out and i'll help you do the same. drop a #metoo down below and i'll be glad to reach out to you. .
.
.
.
.
.
