text:
* s t r o n g • m i n d •
i want every woman to read this book. 
as a victim of sexual abuse in a past relationship, there are many “survival signals,” or red flags, that i wish i had known earlier. knowing the signals would have allowed me to trust my gut instead of rationalizing away my fear. the gift of fear is an empowering book that teaches you how to spot subtle signs of danger and trust your intuition in order to keep yourself safe. i truly believe this book could help save your life someday. ——————
chapter 4 of this book goes over seven survival signals to watch for that will help you know that the other person has bad intentions. this applies whether it is a stranger approaching you and offering help or a first date with a guy off tinder. trust your gut when you see these red flags:

1. forced teaming “the detectable signal of forced teaming is the projecting of a shared purpose or experience where none exists: “both of us”; “we’re some team”; “how are we going to handle this?” etc... forced teaming is done in many contexts for many reasons but when applied by a stranger to a woman in a vulnerable situation (such as alone in an unpopulated area), it is always inappropriate. 
2. charm and niceness “to charm is to compel, to control by allure or attraction. “he was so nice,” is a comment i often hear from people describing the man who, moments or months after his niceness, attacked them. we must learn and teach our children that niceness does not equal goodness... if you consciously tell yourself, “this person is trying to charm me,” as opposed to “this person is charming,” you’ll be able to see around it.” 3. too many details 
4. typecasting 
5. loan sharking 
6. the unsolicited promise
7. ***discounting the word “no”*** “with strangers, even those with the best intentions, never, ever relent on the issue of “no,” because it sets the stage for more efforts to control... when someone ignores that word, ask yourself: why is this person seeking to control me? what does he want?” check out the book the gift of fear by gavin de becker to learn more. i can’t recommend it enough. #metoo #thegiftoffear #domesticviolence #trustyourgut #strongmind #survival

text:
dzisiaj mija termin, w którym zgodnie z prawem mogłam złożyć zażalenie w sprawie umorzenia postępowania dotyczącego gróźb karalnych. miałam na to 7 dni od otrzymania listu. bardzo chciałam to zrobić. znajomy prawnik zaproponował wsparcie. i tu, niestety, koniec sprzyjających okoliczności.

i w kulturze, i w amazonie grudzień jest potwornie intensywny. od poniedziałku pracuję fizycznie 10, a nawet 11 godzin na nockach w magazynie. po powrocie, od 6 rano, pracuję jeszcze nad redakcją, książkami i tekstami. nie miałam czasu zająć się zażaleniem. kolega-prawnik także pracował. nie udało się.

niesprawiedliwy system prawny, zgodnie z którym umarzane są sprawy dotyczące przemocy wobec kobiet, a sprawcy pozostają bezkarni, jest olbrzymim problemem – i trzeba z tym walczyć. ale nie mniejszym problemem jest to, że wiele osób zwyczajnie nie ma czasu na tę walkę. mnóstwo spraw w ogóle nie trafia na policję, a gdy zostaną umorzone, nikt nie składa zażalenia. nie dlatego, że nie ma winy. często też nie dlatego, że kobiety nie chcą ukarania sprawcy. dlatego, że pracują – w korpo/magazynie/biedronce/kulturze. i jeszcze w domu. nie mogą sobie pozwolić na dodatkowe obciążenie: finansowe, czasowe i emocjonalne. a jakoś i z czegoś muszą codziennie żyć.

przemoc wobec kobiet to także przemoc ekonomiczna – codziennie odbiera poczucie bezpieczeństwa i wymusza milczenie. dlatego #metoo to nie tylko walka z przemocą, ale i walka o warunki, w których wszystkie będziemy mogły walczyć z przemocą bez utraty środków do życia, snu i zdrowia psychicznego. to walka o lepsze warunki pracy, krótszy tydzień pracy i więcej czasu wolnego, zabezpieczenia socjalne i darmowy dostęp do publicznych usług zdrowia, opieki i edukacji.

słuchajmy się nawzajem, walczmy za nas wszystkie – by każda mogła się angażować i domagać się swoich praw, nie tylko te, które akurat mają na to warunki.

jak powinna wyglądać skrzywdzona, żebyś jej uwierzył?
może nie złożyć zażalenia na umorzenie dochodzenia w sprawie gróźb karalnych ze względu na nadmierne obciążenie pracą?

text: over the last 2 months, the media has been overwhelmed with cases of sexual assault and extreme miscarriages of justice. from brett kavanaugh, the ireland rape case, cyntoia brown, and now the case out of baylor university. consent is black and white; only yes means yes, and no always means no. survivors of sexual assault are being repeatedly told that their experience doesn’t matter, and that the comfort of the accused is more important. there is such a low rate of reporting sexual assault because survivors not being believed is consistently repeated everywhere due to our broken justice system. statistics show that only 2-5% of reported cases of rape are falsified, so the narrative that “women lie about rape and innocent men shouldn’t have their lives ruined” needs to go. real rapists are barely ever convicted (approx. 6/1000 accused serve jail time), much less innocent men (it does happen, but at extremely low rates). men like jacob walter anderson and brock turner grow up to become the brett kavanaugh’s of the world, so we need to continue to have conversations and teaching consent; while this may be the reality of our past and present, i refuse to believe that this will be our future. hold the people in your world accountable when you see this behaviour being exhibited, because until our justice system begins to properly enact justice for survivors, this is one of the number one ways you can help to create change. every survivor deserves to have their story heard and validated, and every perpetrator deserves to face the full consequences of their actions. #womenhelpingwomen #tampontuesday #grlpwr #feminist #menstruation #womensrights #womenshealth #reproductivehealth #getinvolved #toronto #uoft #womensupportwomen #feminism #instadaily #torontoblogger #torontoevents #2018 #violenceagainstwomen #orangetheworld #metoo #timesup

text:
ever since i watched @brenebrown amazing ted talk i fell in love with the entire ted institution. when i moved back to uganda in jan 2018 i put ted on my vision board. i had no idea how i would get there, or what i would even talk about. i just knew that i wanted to be a part of the global community of like minded people who wished to inspire and be inspired by others. 
when i got the call that i was invited to be a speaker at a ted event i couldn't believe it. that i was chosen out of so many and so early on in my career with my organisation being so young. i was and still am amazed that i ticked off this item on my bucket list so early and easily. 
i will forever be grateful to the amazing people who helped me get here. 
so i raise a toast to my first (hopefully many more to come) ted talk and a toast to never giving up on yourself. cheers ❤

#gratitude #thankful #humbled 
@thehealthacademyug 
__________________________________

on the 7th of december 2018 our founder ameena babirye was one of the speakers at the tedxnaguru event. 
the event was about female empowerment, gender equality and gender based violence. 
ameena gave a talk addressing the importance of heath education in the fight for gender equality. 
it was a great day with many wonderful and inspiring speakers.

text:
so as some of you know, i am currently writing a book titled, you glow, girl! i am so excited about sharing this with you all!  i’ve been writing away and honestly at times it’s not been easy. i’m writing about some extremely emotional and challenging times in my life and being 100% vulnerable. 
i heard a story a while back and this resonated with me as i’m writing today.  it’s about a glow stick. most of you know what a glow stick is and it doesn’t glow by itself until you break it.  just like a glow stick we were created to glow. if we stand still and don’t move, we are not doing what we were created to do.  once a glow stick is broken it starts to glow.  it’s fulfilling its purpose.  i’ve faced many challenges and hardships over the years.  my dad’s battle with cancer, my marriage, my business and there were times i broke down. when i was broken it was bad. but, i had to get up and keep going and with a lot of work i now clearly see what my purpose is. without those trials and tribulations how would i know? how can you see the good when you don’t know the bad?  we were all created to glow and sometimes we need to break before we can shine. xo  #youglowgirl
name: Beth Wilson-Parentice

text:
#miracomosnosponemos  las actrices argentinas se han unido para gritar contra las agresiones sexuales que sufren en la industria. más de cincuenta profesionales entre las que se encuentran cecilia roth, lali espósito, julieta ortega y calu rivero se presentaron ayer en una rueda de prensa para denunciar los abusos de los que son víctimas. las actrices respaldaron en público a thelma fardín, después de que publicara un vídeo en el que acusaba al actor juan darthés de violarla hace 9 años en nicaragua cuando ella tenía tan solo 16 años y ambos estaban de gira con la popular serie “patito feo”. "es un fenómeno que ha sacudido internacionalmente la industria del espectáculo y es funcional a ella. hoy decimos ‘basta’. la impunidad de los abusadores debe terminar”, han reclamado.
.

text: “dear any man on this feed, if you see my daughters during the holidays, do not: ruffle their hair. do not pick them up and swing them over your head. do not pick them up, period. do not tickle them. do not stick your fingers into their stomach and tell them they're pretty. do not tell them they're pretty, period. do not tell them you like their dress. do not comment on their appearance, period. do not mention princesses. do not comment on how much food they're eating. it's possible, man on this feed, that your intentions come from a kind place. you were told that telling a little girl she is pretty and picking her up is just what men do. guess what: it's not. every time i see you touch my daughters at a holiday party, i sit them down at home afterwards say: "did your body feel comfortable when that man you didn't know poked you in your sides?" i say: "did it give you a creepy vibe when that man you never met touched your cheek and said you looked like a little dolly?" i say: "no man who you don't know should ever touch you and if they do and it’s creepy i want you to say 'don't touch me i don't like that' in a big strong voice like simba's daddy (sadly i cannot think of a female disney character who has a bold voice) and walk away." here is what is okay to say to my daughters, man on this feed: "hi, nice to meet you, can i give you a fist bump or a high five?" ask them what they're reading in school. ask what movies they’ve seen. help me help my daughters understand that their bodies belong to them, and no one else. help me teach my daughters to speak up and out should someone ever threaten the skin they're in. no one did this with me when i was a little girl; i had to learn the hard way. oh the stories i could tell you — don't make me.” ~ rg via @mollyrosenguy via @stonefoxbride #teachyourchildrenwell #metoo #thefutureisfemalemovement

text:
i've been feeling a pull to write lately.
.
typically this really only happens when i'm in a traumatic state.
.
i turn to poetry as a form of expression when my emotions are overwhelming.
.
like when a national tragedy occurs.
.
but lately the pull to write happens when i'm feeling joyful, excited, and creative!
.
the things i write are surprisingly less about creativity and more about grounding and harnessing those moments of inspiration.
.
i've also been feeling a pull toward feminine power.
.
recognizing my admiration for women who embrace their innate strength and identifying my own powerful femininity has been empowering.
.
i've been particularly drawn toward the power of the female body.
.
acknowledging the beauty of pregnancy and childbirth as well as the mental and physical fortitude that is required for raising children, has given me an intense sense of gratitude for what my body is capable of.
.
it makes me very proud to be a woman.
.
it makes me feel capable and a sense of sacred strength and beauty.
.
i feel connected to the universe in a raw spectacular way.
.
💖🌌🌕🌠
#madeofstardust #freespirit #femininepower #flowerchild

from cnn: - u.s. capitol hill

text:
меган фокс высказалась против движения #metoo

когда звезды голливуда объявляли войну домогательствам в киноиндустрии и друг за другом рассказывали о том, как страдали от харассмента, актриса меган фокс не была замечена на передовой движения #metoo. в недавнем разговоре с корреспондентом new york times 32-летняя звезда "трансформеров" ( transformers) объяснила, почему так произошло.

актриса не стала детально описывать случаи домогательств в своей жизни, но при этом заявила, что их было предостаточно. фокс пожаловалась, что еще до массового всплеска общественного негодования выступала против подобного отношения к женщине, но получила разочарование: ее никто не поддержал.

text:
i’m in a completely new space. my heart is stronger, my discipline is stronger. i have found myself crossing the same subtle cycles all year and i no longer accept this. i cut cords and have walked away from every single person who makes me feel lesser and unworthy of their love. 
i have decided that i will no longer delve in the emotional labor of other men so that they may heal themselves through me. i have blocked off all easy roads leading to me. i have distanced myself so far from mediocre attention and lusts that do not meet my soul. i demand much more from my relationships these days than i did when i was a child. i have woken up to my grace & i rejoice in the sanctuary that i have built of myself. 
i am not for these lesser men, it took me a while to accept it but i will not pay homage through another mans broken heart again. #oathtoself #vows #inlove #withme #healing #metoo #ramblingsofagypsy

text:
hoy durante el día me quedé pensando mucho en "no es no" pero sabés qué?! no me representa ni quiero eso para mis hijas (son tres). ser mujer no tiene implícito un sí, que es una etapa previa al decir no. .
.
no, no tenés derecho a mirarnos como quieras, a desnudarnos simplemente con la mirada.

no, no podés darnos un beso y un abrazo porque se te ocurrió que estaba bien, mucho menos sentarnos en tu regazo o apoyarnos nada.

no, no podés tocarnos o decirnos algo porque se te pasó por tu mente si lo que tenés para decir es simplemente tu deseo enfermo. .
.
no, no somos objetos de deseo hechos para complacer a cualquiera que tenga algo más de fuerza o poder que nosotras y tenga ganas de jodernos.

no, no nos vestimos para que nos desees ni provocarte nada.

no, no tenés que esperar a que te digamos que no, nunca te dijimos sí.

no antes de ser no nunca fue un si, no estaba implícito en ser mujer o menor, no te confundas.

ser papá, tío, primo, maestro, hermano, director, pastor, sacerdote, conocido o desconocido no te da ningún derecho sobre nosotras. nunca fue si, no nos hagas pedirte por favor no.

me pasó a mí y ya le pasó a una de mis hijas, #nuncafuesi no te confundas! .
.
.
.
(foto de manuel gayoso)
#noesno #niunamenos #miracomonosponemos #amimepaso #yotecreo #juntassomosmais #juntas #niunamas #metoo

i’m sorry to get serious on this page during such a festive and joyous time of year, but i just wanted to remind everyone to look out for one another at every christmas party and new years event ❤️ladies: be mindful of your drink, be mindful of the space, be mindful of one another.
 men (and women) who may be thinking of taking advantage of any of theses factors:  do not sexually assault/ harass / manipulate / take advantage of / control people. simple. i know this illustration means so much more than just staying safe at parties and/or while drinking- but i just wanted to touch on it because everyone is entitled to a safe and fun holiday season ❤️ one day this won’t be a thing. one day. sending lots of light and love. -

text:
ayer leía con terror,ira, y mucha tristeza  miles de comentarios de mujeres y hombres que por un lado justificaban la violación sexual cometida a la actriz thelma.
en algunos comentarios decían: “¿que hace una piba con un short en el cuarto de un hombre mayor?”, o que las actrices que apoyan el movimiento son unas “exhibicionistas y trabajan con su cuerpo”, como si trabajar con la imagen, ser modelo, actriz, una persona del común que suba una foto, o el sólo hecho de ser mujer y salir con un vestido o lo que sea que queramos utilizar, les estemos diciendo “te autorizo para me violes, me acoses, me manosees”.
así mismo, otras personas hacen referenccia a la divulgación tarde de este tipo de violencia sexual como algo para adquirir fama, como si ser violada fuera la mejor cosa que nos pudiera pasar, y no quedara un trauma tan grave que sencillamente quisiéramos no hablar de esto para superarlo, por miedo por lo que sea que cada persona sienta que le impida decirlo; y cuando por fin podemos hacerlo, “somos oportunistas, mentirosas, falsas” olvidando que a uds no les ha pasado, no lo han vivido. 
pero si no sabes, cuando esto sucede, uno se culpa, ¿porque fui a visitar a mi familia?, ¿por qué no me quede en casa?, ¿por qué salí?,¿por qué a mí?.
y no, no es mí culpa, no es tú culpa. a la mierda con ese pensamiento, hemos tenido que ir al psicólogo, al psiquiatra por el sólo hecho de que un ser, o varios, no entiendan que “nuestro cuerpo, no les pertenece, es de nosotras/os”, nadie tiene el derecho de elegir sobre este, más que nosotras, que si nos vestimos como queremos no es porque queremos provocarte, porque te estamos pidiendo que nos jodas la vida. 
deja de justificar la violencia sexual como si el victimario pasara a ser una víctima, porque el no es quien carga con los malos recuerdos, las pesadillas, la incomodidad con el cuerpo, con la depresión, con el querer morirse, con el no poder desarrollarse con total libertad.
ya no más de culparnos, ya hemos tenido suficiente. lo que nos hicieron, no nos define #miracómonosponemos #metoo a los 7 y a los 17 años. 
si te pasa algo llama a la línea 123 y solicita ayuda
no estas sol@

en algunos comentarios decían: “¿que hace una piba con un sho en el cuao de un hombre mayor?”, o que las actrices que apoyan el movimiento son unas “exhibicionistas y trabajan con su cuerpo”, como si trabajar con la imagen, ser modelo, actriz, una persona del común que suba una foto, o el sólo hecho de ser mujer y salir con un vestido o lo que sea que queramos utilizar, les estemos diciendo “te autorizo para me violes, me acoses, me manosees”.
así mismo, otras personas hacen referenccia a la divulgación tarde de este tipo de violencia sexual como algo para adquirir fama, como si ser violada fuera la mejor cosa que nos pudiera pasar, y no quedara un trauma tan grave que sencillamente quisiéramos no hablar de esto para superarlo, por miedo por lo que sea que cada persona sienta que le impida decirlo; y cuando por fin podemos hacerlo, “somos opounistas, mentirosas, falsas” olvidando que a uds no les ha pasado, no lo han vivido. 
pero si no sabes, cuando esto sucede, uno se culpa, ¿porque fui a visitar a mi familia?, ¿por qué no me quede en casa?, ¿por qué salí?,¿por qué a mí?.
y no, no es mí culpa, no es tú culpa. a la mierda con ese pensamiento, hemos tenido que ir al psicólogo, al psiquiatra por el sólo hecho de que un ser, o varios, no entiendan que “nuestro cuerpo, no les peenece, es de nosotras/os”, nadie tiene el derecho de elegir sobre este, más que nosotras, que si nos vestimos como queremos no es porque queremos provocae, porque te estamos pidiendo que nos jodas la vida. 
deja de justificar la violencia sexual como si el victimario pasara a ser una víctima, porque el no es quien carga con los malos recuerdos, las pesadillas, la incomodidad con el cuerpo, con la depresión, con el querer morirse, con el no poder desarrollarse con total libead.
ya no más de culparnos, ya hemos tenido suficiente. lo que nos hicieron, no nos define   a los 7 y a los 17 años. 
si te pasa algo llama a la línea 123 y solicita ayuda
no estas sol@

text:
at very first, i would like to thank my ex, who literally had made my life a living hell. and because of that breakup period in my life, i got to know who i was and who i should have been. i basically wasn't very close to my friends before this. but when he broke up with me, i was totally shattered and there comes the role of my mother (who basically stood by me in each and every part of my life, since forever.
.
and i don't want to talk about her favours in my life, because they are uncountable. she is not only great mother but also an amazing woman), other than my mother i got to know who my real friends were. the people whom i had sent away because of a stupid relationship, stood by me all through the while and were ready to do anything and everything to make me laugh. then, because of the breakup i got to know the definition of self love, confidence and feminism. i got the true love of my life.
.
a guy who is incredibly amazing, a guy who is nothing like my ex, a guy who made me believe in love once again. and then i would like to thank my father, though he is with me but initially we had differences in our relationship, so because of that i became bold, as from the very beginning of my age i had started to do everything alone, i started to go out alone n do all the stuff necessary for me. i made contacts with several people. and that made me quite an extrovert person.
.
so, basically i would like to thank my mother (mrs. anita singh), my boyfriend (indrajeet @indrajeet_mishra), my friends (mansi @__mansivimal, saif @saif.apk,  shefali @shefali_25_) and myself for rebuilding me and keeping my happiness above their own happiness. no offense to my father, but he just didn't serve everything in my life, hence i had to work for achieving everything in my life, which is a good thing and it made me stronger.
.
- from shivangi anita singh @tani1524

text_retweet:
as a white woman i have existed in many white feminist spaces and worked in many white feminist circles. i’m going to be honest, it took time for me to understand why what i was experiencing didn’t feel quite right. it wasn’t until i started making accountable relationships with women of color and following the lead of activists of color/orgs led by them, that i realized how violent white feminists are. i began to notice the harmful/violent behaviors my friends were talking about all around me: tokenism, tone-policing, white tears, distancing/ self proclaimed innocence, scapegoating (“my husbands black” or “i volunteer in the black neighborhood”), the belief that one can be “done” learning about oppression and racism esp amongst older women(“i participated in the civil rights movement. i’m not racist”), etc. 
_______________
this is all textbook white feminism but the problem is that white women aren’t reading the book. we put blinders on when it comes to analyzing how we ourselves contribute to systems of oppression. this is dangerous to women of color and trans women who are fighting for their right to survive under this oppressive system. this is a major problem because this behavior is present in our government, our nonprofits, our schools, our charity organizations, our foundations, our social service institutions, our social justice movements/activist spaces- everywhere. by only upholding white perspectives and white voices within our spaces we contribute to white supremacy and oppressive institutions by ignoring other oppressions.
_______________
white feminism is inescapable. it’s up to us to call it out and call these ladies in to discuss racist behavior and sentiments within these spaces. and be willing to be called in and listen when people have criticism or suggestions for us as well. trust me it’s wildly uncomfortable. but it’s so necessary. it gets easier with practice. i have fumbled through many times. but this is our charge. we have to do it.
________________
repost @whitemalefeminist 
#whitefeminism #intersectionalfeminism #womanism #whitewomen #soundsaboutwhite #feminist #livelaughlove #antiracism #racialjustice #socialjustice #speakout #metoo

text:
🔥 saiu o instagram's top trends de 2018 🤩
ㅤ
com 2018 quase chegando ao fim, o instagram do facebook destacou algumas tendências do ano e compartilhou todas as maneiras pelas quais a comunidade do instagram usou a plataforma para se expressar.
ㅤ
de acordo com o instagram, compartilhar amor e bondade ainda é uma prioridade para a comunidade no instagram: o heart love sticker de arata foi o adesivo do giphy mais usado em stories, enquanto heart eyes foi o filtro de rosto mais usado em stories. em feed, o emoji ❤ "coração" foi usado em comentários mais de 14 bilhões de vezes. o lugar mais feliz do mundo? disneyland tokyo, que também teve o maior uso do emoji 🙂 "sorriso" no texto da legenda.
ㅤ
o instagram é o lugar de inúmeros interesses e comunidades; este ano, a asmr foi a principal tendência da comunidade de nichos do ano, continuando a aumentar a sua popularidade.
ㅤ
o jogo fortnite também teve um crescimento explosivo, com a #fortnite sendo a hashtag que mais cresce no mundo. o domínio do k-pop nas mídias sociais é refletido pelo bts “army” sendo a principal comunidade de fãs na plataforma.
ㅤ
o maior desafio de dança viral do ano também nasceu no instagram, com #inmyfeelingschallenge, que incluiu todos, de @theshiggyshow a @willsmith, chegando ao número 1.

por último, mas não menos importante, milhões de pessoas usaram o instagram para fazer suas vozes serem ouvidas em 2018. as principais hashtags do ano foram #metoo (1,5 milhão), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k).
ㅤ
ㅤ
resumo de 2018 no instagram:
ㅤ
● filtro de rosto mais usado em histórias no instagram: heart eyes
● gif do giphy mais usado nas histórias no instagram: heart love sticker by arata
● número de vezes que o emoji ❤ "coração" foi usado nos comentários: 14 bilhões
● o lugar mais feliz do mundo (e com maior uso do emoji 🙂 "sorriso" na legenda): disneyland tokyo
● tendência da comunidade de nicho: asmr
● hashtag com maior crescimento: #fortnite
● comunidade fandom: bts (#btsarmy)
● top dance movement: #inmyfeelingschallenge
● principais hashtags usadas por uma causa: #metoo (1,5 milhões), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k)
ㅤ
ㅤ
e você o que achou do ano de 2018 no instagram?
fez parte d

text:
en estos días tan movilizantes, no queríamos dejar de mencionar desde nuestro colectivo @versafc la discriminación que recibimos las mujeres en el deporte en general, y en el fútbol en particular. la escasez de oportunidades para jugar profesional, las dificultades de asistir a alentar a nuestro equipo de fútbol por los riesgos que eso nos conlleva (acoso, burlas), las diferencias en las condiciones laborales si surgiese la vacante en un equipo y las constantes comparaciones que recibimos sobre cómo jugamos por debajo a como juegan los hombres, son algunos de los ejemplos con los que las mujeres debemos lidiar a diario en el ambiente del fútbol. en la mayoría de las ocasiones nos llevan a la burla y al ridiculo, exigiéndonos que juguemos igual a cómo juegan los hombres cuando ellos nos llevan más de 20 años de ventaja en este deporte. muchas de nosotras hoy tocamos por primera vez una pelota porque perdimos el miedo, no nos importa la mirada juzgadora del patriarcado, y sabemos que podemos lograr todo lo que nos propongamos.
 más unidas, más solidarias, más compañeras, más hermanas que nunca 💚✊🏽 sororidad #miracononosponemos  #noesno #metoo #feministas #feminismo #feminist #abortolegal #sevaacaer #ahoraqueestamosjuntas #futbol #football #futbolfemenino

text:
some days i am not mentally nor physically ready for a full practice. just sun salutations and finishing poses was my practice today. .
yesterday i had a big fever so i needed to take it easier physically. also mentally this week has been extremely challenging. a sexual scandal bursted in the ashtanga world that touches me very deeply as it involves my very first ashtanga teacher. and i keep asking myself “why?” “why does this happen so often?” “why does make this people behave like animals?” at least i am extremely proud of the ones who overcame their fears, stood strong and reported the situation. well done strong and powerful ladies! .

text:
i thought it might be super fun to do 10 random facts about myself...⠀
⠀
1.  i had bright blue eyes up until i was about 6 years old when they changed to a greenish-hazel. ⠀
2. i hate banana's so much that the smell of walking passed them in the grocery store can even makes me gag. 3. i am an only child and i am adopted. ⠀
4. my favorite part of the pizza are those little bubbles in the crust. i will always pick them off and eat them first. ⠀
5. jeopardy is an all time favorite and i love making star wars laser gun noises when the daily double is selected.⠀
6. i was an extremely picky eater growing up, until the year i got married. we went to a lot of ethnic dinner parties and i didn't want to seem rude. turns out, i liked most of it. ⠀
7.  i used to love milk...no more like obsessed with it. turn's out i'm lactose intolerant (and allergic to soy) and now i have to drink almond milk. but every once and a while i try the real thing again, and i don't even like the taste anymore.⠀
8. i'm super allergic to beets. like tongue swells and can't breathe, kind of allergy. you'd think it's not a big deal but turn's out 50% of the worlds sugar is made from beets, and is used a lot to create an all natural red dye. i'll never be able to have cherry popsicle's. ⠀
9.  i can rap eminem's lose yourself in its entirety without it playing in the background. ⠀
10. it's pop, not soda. ⠀
bonus fact. my favorite food in the world is a moroccan dish called rfissa, it has like 10,000 calories per serving and usually is only served in celebration of the birth of a baby. i'd gladly get pregnant just for a bite of that deliciousness. ⠀
⠀
⠀

text: “we curled up on the love seat together, his arm around me, and we watched several episodes before his mom popped her head into the room and asked if we wanted dessert. she stood momentarily in the doorway before returning downstairs. a few minutes later, instead of his mom returning with our plates, noah’s dad came up. he walked into the room with a plate in each hand and stood there with the giddiest, most genuinely excited smile on his face. he remained like that for an uncomfortable amount of time before remembering to hand us our plates. once he finished his assignment, he stood back, smiling once again. he began to walk from the room but stopped just at the doorway until noah’s mom, who had been standing in the hallway, pulled him away. i leaned over closer to noah and whispered, “they think we’re cute.” “yep. they’ve been standing there for twenty minutes. i feel like i’m in middle school again,” noah softly replied, giving me a playful squeeze. we watched several more episodes, completing the first disk, until it was time for another crowther christmas tradition, which, for noah, was meeting up with his best friend dorian for a movie.” -r. macceile candy apple butterscotch: a memoir available now! #fourstars #memoir #metoo #ptsdsurvivor “it’s worth the read it’s about a #woman #empowered and my god that is a #wonderful thing indeed” #linkinbio #authorsofinstagram #independentpublishing #goodreads #newbookalert #readforfree now - dec 25th 100% of proceeds from my books go entirely toward my #holiday #charity #fundraiser benefiting the #afsp you can find more info on rebeccasbookshop.com be sure to check out @thattinywebsite and @eveyjacob contributions too!

text:
krokodilov centar za savremenu književnost
karađorđeva 43, ulaz iz bašte 
26. decembar, sreda, 19 sati 
gigantomahija ili krokodilov duel u tri runde na temu: "#metoo pokret u svetu i kod nas: novo osnaživanje ili novi puritanizam." učestvuju: dubravka stojanović i biljana srbljanović.
cena ulaznice u pretprodaji 300 dinara a 500 dinara s konzumacijom jednog pića po izboru. cena ulaznice na vratima na dan događaja 500 dinara s konzumacijom jednog pića po izboru.
ulaznice se mogu kupiti u krokodilovom centru svakog dana od 10 do 22 časa izuzev nedeljom (od 16 do 22 časa).
pokret protiv seksualnog nasilja #metoo izazvao je brojne kontraverze tokom prethodne godine i može se smatrati jednim od najvažnijih označitelja godine koja je na izmaku.
ova inicijativa koju su pokrenule žrtve seksualnog nasilja proširila se od sad na druge države sveta, a nakon što su brojne i poznate glumice priznale da su na počecima karijere bile žrtve reditelja, kolega ili producenata pokret je dobio na globalnom zamahu. nakon što se otkrilo da su poznati i uticajni muškarci, poput filmskog producenta harveya weinsteina seksualno zlostavljali glumice i koleginice, mnoge žene su obelodanile sopstvene ispovesti.
iako je nesumnjivo reč o talasu novog oslobođenja, nesumnjivo preko potrebnog ženama širom planete, ujedno je paralelno stvorena i atmosfera intenzivnog lova na veštice pa je opravdano pitanje opasnosti od predominacije novog oblika puritanizma koji više od svih i svega zapravo ponajviše odgovara globalnom političkom i ekonomskom mejnstrimu. 
o pozitivnim i negativnim implikacijama ovog fenomena raspravljaće istoričarka dubravka stojanović i dramska spisateljica biljana srbljanović na novom izdanju gigantomahije, krokodilovog duela u tri runde.
--

liz has over 30 years’ experience in hr. she is a fellow of the cipd and a member of the coaching academy.
liz has held a number of hr director positions including for planet hollywood, regus and tmp worldwide, where she was a member of the leadership team and a board director.
liz particularly enjoys helping employees work through their problems and challenges towards a positive outcome. she is also interested in assessing how companies work and the culture they create, and is passionate about helping them create a better place for their employees.

text:
le nouvel épisode est en ligne ! 🙊
le deuxième de la thématique "les temps forts de ma vie" dans lequel je vous parle cette fois de mes 13 ans.

13 ans, l'âge auquel j'ai réussi à dire #non 👊 l’âge où j’ai acté le fait que cela devait s’arrêter. 
vous l’avez compris, dans ce podcast je parle de ce qui m'a touchée sans langue de bois, sans détour, et ce pour une bonne raison que je ne répéterai jamais assez : donner l'envie aux femmes, aux filles, de se battre, d'aller de l'avant. 💪👉🌞 et pour cela, il faut pouvoir regarder les choses en face, nommer un chat un chat et se reconnaître victime avant de pouvoir passer à l’étape suivante. 
la première étape était celle de l’acceptation du fait d’avoir été victime. et ensuite ? je savais que je ne pouvais rien changer à tout ce que j’avais déjà vécu. mais surtout, j’ai compris que j’avais le pouvoir de dire non. non !

et vous ? 😘😘😘 lien pour écouter dans la bio 🤗

photos : de 10 ans... à 13 ans! savoir souffler les bougies de la vie 🤩 (vous noterez le rouge à lèvre, les bijoux et le vernis à ongle. déjà à l'époque je sentais que je voulais être comédienne. l'un des prochains sujets dans la thématique "et la vie pro dans tout ça ?") #podcasting #spotifypodcast #itunespodcast #woman #metoo #kids #child #rebelion #rebel #fighting #abusesurvivor #survivor #survivors #kidsfighting #childcare #rebelle #rebels #fightclub #fightlikeagirl

"the three wise women" flips the conceit of the "the three wise men" who offer gifts to baby jesus.  queen emerald offers the gift of strength via her golden potatoes, queen sapphire offers the gifts of wisdom  and harmony via the yin yang fish , and queen ruby offers  hope with her fresh loaf of marzipan stollen.  the trio's journey ,  mirrors the trajectory of women over the past several decades. for decades women have struggled to share their gifts with the world. the three wise women finally arrive at a place where they can rightfully share their gifts, talent, and compassion with the world.  at this time in our history, women are  blossoming like never before, which is why i placed giant blossom crowns on the heads. these blossoms are made from discarded bibles which is why artist robert mosley calls them bible blossoms. thank you to my lovely cast jenn liu, ruby lee dove iii, and kenia romero.  special thanks to georgio chaplin for the eye catching costumes. mahalo @tysonsuzuki for managing post. and danke charles bice bey for your seamless editing and rich sound design. and thank you darling nikki!3wisewomen #dtla @bloomartla #dtlaartsdistrict #happeningindtla #dtlaartsdistrict #coldplay #christmas #metoo #blacklivesmatter #la @msjliu @keniarosemary @queenrubylee @blakeyoungfountain @tysonsuzuki #chrismartin #chrismartinfans #lajewelrydistrict #lajewelry #dtlaart #dtlanightlife #dtlaartwalk #laweekly

text:
5 places to look for dresses:⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1.your closet. all you really need for dressember is one dress! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2. a friend’s closet. gather up a few friends and swap dresses once you’re done wearing them. all the money you’re saving on dresses can be donated to your campaign! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3.thrift stores. try a local thrift store in your area to breathe new life into inexpensive, quality finds. you could also try an online thrift store like thred up. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4.rent a dress. you can use dress rental services such as rent the runway for special events. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
5. elegantees (website). check out their dressember line of dresses, which are made by survivors of human trafficking in nepal. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
no matter how you style your dresses, wear them with confidence! you are changing the world right where you are, and that's a big deal.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

.
el machismo en general no se limita a los hombres, la reflexión también debe ser de nosotras, porque somos las primeras en atacarnos  o ¿no han visto fotos sexy de alguna chica y los comentarios negativos de otras mujeres? incluso a la misma que hizo la declaración más reciente, entraron a su cuenta a buscar una foto sexy vieja para a acusarla de provocadora ... las mujeres tenemos mucho machismo.
.  el mismo que se inculca con comentarios como: "tu allá y yo acá", "lo hace porque es hombre", "¿cuántas novias vas a tener?" "los hombres no lloran" ... comentarios machista que se le hacen a los niños que se le quedan, y que por suerte empieza a cambiar y crear conciencia.
. 
y por otro lado ¿ por qué desvincular a los hombres que se quieren sumar a esta causa? debe ser de todos, porque el cambio debe ser social y dejarlo solo al ámbito femenino aumenta una grieta o especie de guerra de géneros que no es la idea original.

#miracomonosponemos 
no es no 
#metoo 
arriba esas mujeres que hablan, que tienen la voz de decir lo que han vivido. apoyo desde el fondo de mi corazón todo lo que está sucediendo en argentina. necesitamos más mujeres que hablen y que se unan y que no se juzguen ....... la realidad es que aunque no haya vuelto a tocar el tema es verdad que solamente hoy puedo decirles que no es no y eso ya les dice mucho. una violación nunca será culpa de la víctima jamás debemos de culparlas,dejemos de nosotros como víctimas de culparnos, no importa cuanto tiempo te haya tomado el hablar lo importante es que has hablado hayan pasado los años que hayan pasado has tenido la valentía de hablar y de denunciar. 
mis respetos y todo mi amor y apoyo a thelma fardin @soythelmafardin  dejemos claro que no es no, y es hora de que la gente se entere que ninguna víctima de abusó sexual se siente contenta o feliz de admitir haber sido ultrajada. y me uno con thelma porque como victimas de una violacion no debemos de dejar esto impune, no no es no.  ni nos debe de dar pena hablar de esto no debemos de callar más. #metoo  seamos más mujeres que se unan en contra de estos violadores, abusadores y sobretodo psicopatas que necesitan estar detrás de las rejas, hoy puede ser ella,hace unos años fui yo, pero mañana puede ser tú hermana, tu mamá o tu hija, así que no es no ! @actrices.argentinas  #metoo @gainfante  @saleelsoltv  @jessysototv  @tvynovelasmex @revistatvnotas  @alessandrardlv  @emmanuelduprez @hijodevecino 
no es no mujeres mexicanas unámonos con nuestras hermanas argentinas que han sabido unirse con esto. no es no ! y un golpe como el que también recibí por mi ultrajador también es una violencia que mexico cómo país no debería de haber promovido ni haber hecho que esta persona tuviera voz para hablar cuando me había golpeado enfrente de 300 personas, no es no. cuando lo entenderán ?? sobre qué he hecho a nivel legal no hablaré del tema por el momento, solamente me uno al movimiento y me uno con mi corazón y toda mi valentía para sumarme a estas valientes mujeres.

text:
#barbietoo  before i left the house i made sure to dress in something loose that would not be too distracting. as i walk the streets of new york at night,one hand holds my groceries tightly, the other holds my pocket knife. i walk with urgency, my hoodie is up and my headphones in and,which are not playing music, act like a barrier between the men who catcalls and whistles at me. i see a masculine shadow at the end of the street, but i cannot see its owner. i fear it’s a man awaiting my passing. i make a detour and walk across the street. 
as i usually do on a weekend night, i was clubbing and hanging out with my girls. i normally go to gay clubs, but this weekend i went to a straight club.  once i felt a strong grip on my ass, i turned around to say what the hell, but this 6 foot tall frat guy in a polo would not look at me. this is the first time i  had my ass grabbed unsolicitedly. they have the balls to grab me, but they don’t own up to their actions. every 5 minutes i would take a headcount of my girls because the cocky boys would not listen to us when we said we did not want to grind with them. this was the first night where i saw that the boys were not listening to no. it made me wonder why they felt because it was dark and the music was loud that they could do what they want. i was not being listened to. “there is no greater threat to women than men? we’re the number one threat!” said louis c.k. in his hbo special. when are men taught to acknowledge boundaries? i should be able to leave and feel safe wherever i go without having to worry. i am tired with the way that men are treating me and other women. every women has there own story with harassment, but to tell mine i am using barbie as my proxy. when i was younger i looked up to her and she was a beacon of indepence and i vividly remember watching rapunzel barbie in my bubblegum pink room thinking “look at all that she can do for herself”. #photo #photography #art #camera #canon #fujifilm #fujitx1 #digital #digitalphoto #digitalphotography #digitalphotos #mirrorless #metoo #barbie #pink #hair #violent #ken #sexualassult

text:
don't read this one.
maybe just have a seat and be quiet until the dark leaves.
we will have a drink or two, 
and then look at the stars all night through.
maybe just let things be.
just don't fucking read this
or me.
i am a poet.
a messy one.
a broken one.
i will tell you, how your life matters and assure you things would be better.
but i will never tell you how i do not keep objects near me.
objects that can cut your soul and rip your heart into pieces.
in a fear that i would cut the vein running through my wrist in an attempt to 
see how numbness gushes out with the blood.
it would feel good.
'what a hypocrite?'
you would scoff.
i will hold you 
tell you to share your stories with me,
stories that haunt you.
and do not let you sleep.
but i would never tell you how every night
i text a random hi to five different names
hoping they would revert,
and always end up begging 
strangers on instagram 
strangers as fucked up as me 
to share some of the gnawing pain.
i am a poet.
a broken one, you see.
'fake' ,
you would look away.
i will look at the slits on your wrist,
and scold you for doing this.
while caressing them till they heal.
but silently wish,
that you knew,
how wrists and arms are not the only place that can be cut.
sometimes it is deep within.
deep within.
where no one can see the hurt.
but it does not matter,
i have all the answers.
and have got it all sorted.
because i am a poet, you see.
'fix yourself before fixing others', you scream.
i wish that were as easy.
and you would get up and begin to leave.
'stay', i would whisper.
'damn you',you screech.
you left behind a poet,
you see.
a broken one.
a messy one.
i told you not to read,
now see,
like umpteen others,
who promised to stay
till the sun rises,
you left before the dark could even leave.
.
.
arunima sengupta.
(@adding_soul_to_words)
.
.
.

the only thing more detrimental than society’s unreal expectations on how woman should look, are the abiding women who perpetuate these stereotypes.
.

if we cannot stop scorning the ones wielding the flame?
~ @mazadohta .
.
i cannot stress this enough. #womensupportwomen .
.
stop judging each other and begin to talk to one another.
understanding builds bridges. .
don’t take from each other. extend your hand and help and hold each other up.
.
lastly,
treat each other with respect. there is room for everyone to grow, give each other the recognition for who they are and what they bring forth.
.

text: "the three wise women" flips the conceit of the "the three wise men" who offer gifts to baby jesus.  queen emerald offers the gift of strength via her golden potatoes, queen sapphire offers the gifts of wisdom  and harmony via the yin yang fish , and queen ruby offers  hope with her fresh loaf of marzipan stollen.  the trio's journey ,  mirrors the trajectory of women over the past several decades. for decades women have struggled to share their gifts with the world. the blossom crowns  are made from discarded bibles which is why artist robert mosley calls them bible blossoms. for more info:  https://www.bloomartla.com/ thank you to my lovely cast  jenn liu,  ruby lee dove iii, and kenia romero.  special thanks to georgio chaplin for the eye catching costumes. mahalo @tysonsuzuki  for managing post. and danke  charles bice bey for your seamless editing and rich sound design. and thank you darling nikki!3wisewomen #dtla @bloomartla #dtlaartsdistrict #happeningindtla #dtlaartsdistrict #coldplay #christmas #metoo #blacklivesmatter #la @msjliu @keniarosemary @queenrubylee @blakeyoungfountain @tysonsuzuki #chrismartin #chrismartinfans #lajewelrydistrict #lajewelry #dtlaart #dtlanightlife #dtlaartwalk #laweekly @vconline @evoke_yoga #goddess #goddessvibes @thesmallshopla @guampdn @kuamnews @lacma @lastbookstorela

text:
being vegan is so easy once you understand why you are! sounds odd but ask yourself why do you choose one thing over another?

ego is often the reason people use to make for their choices. admitting to this will kick your butt into gear! no more empty decisions, if your don't agree but are choosing to say yes because of fear that you won't be liked/accepted/confronted then your ego has you by the short and curly's!

be 100% and you will make yourself proud!

text:
▪️"en france, environ 225 000 femmes sont chaque année victimes de violences conjugales.
en 2017, une femme est morte tous les trois jours sous les coups de son compagnon."
la maltraitance, dans toutes ses formes, est l'affaire de tous, c'est pourquoi ce combat est aussi l'un des nôtres.
oz-bijoux, la première ligne de bijoux de sécurité, est né de cette volonté, de cette envie de lutter contre ce fléau, autrement, et à notre façon.
devant une telle urgence, il est parfois impossible, voir dangereux, de saisir son téléphone devant son agresseur.
votre bijou sera toujours à portée de main, et toujours prêt à l'emploi où que vous soyez.
c'est un bijou bienveillant, un compagnon de confiance où la technologie se charge de tout, bien au delà de ce que l'humain peut faire, jusqu'à pouvoir sauver des vies. ➡️ le double clic donne immédiatement votre position géographique à 5 personnes de votre choix, et les alerte par sms, appel et e-mail simultanément. ces contacts pourront également se coordonner entre eux pour vous porter secours. ➡️ le clic prolongé déclenche, durant 1h sans interruption une sirène d'alarme attirant l'attention sur vous, ou bien active l'enregistrement de votre environnement sonore, pour confondre votre agresseur auprès des tribunaux. l'enregistrement est recevable, et à l'appréciation du juge.▪️ ne requiert aucun abonnement. 🌐 plus d'infos sur www.oz-bijoux.com
sources: @madamefigarofr / #avft​ http://bit.ly/2sndwnn
------------------------------

text: bild från arkivet, två veckor sedan. mycket har redan sagts om dammen brister-boken. kanske att den är onödig (varför vältra sig i våldshistorier) eller att den är för gräll (varför göra en så snygg bok om en så allvarlig sak). vi tyckte inte heller att det var oproblematiskt att göra boken. men nu ligger den på mitt fönsterbräde, som en påminnelse. om att stöda och att prata och att ställa krav. och jag är lycklig att bokhyllorna får ha den här boken och att vinsten går till mödra- och skyddshem. det är tung läsning men det är allvar och jag är stolt över att boken finns! #dammenbrister #metoo

text:
karmic soulmates example

december 13, 2018👉swipe for synastry chart

emily ratajkowski and sebasian bear-mcclard are an example of a karmic soulmate relationship. i have analyzed both of their dates, times and locations of birth to create a brief sample of their astro synastry chart & report. her planets are on the left and his planets are on the right. the angle between the planets is in the middle. 
emily 6/7/91  sebastian 3/27/87

moon conjunct north node=soulmates
moon conjunct sun=emotional understanding
sun conjunct chiron=healing the ego
uranus conjunct neptune=telepathic communication
venus quincunx moon=feeling underappreciated
pluto opposite mars=arguments
chiron conjunct descendant=karmic relationship
saturn square pluto=power struggle
sun quincunx pluto=transformation
venus trine sun=shared values
uranus square sun=unpredictable relationship

emily and sebastian are soulmates. her moon is conjunct his north node. the moon is our emotions, nurturing and vulnerability. the north node is our life purpose in this lifetime. the angle is conjunct or 0° creating an intensity. the moon has qualities that the north node person needs to complete their life purpose. this is also a karmic relationship. her chiron is conjunct his descendant. chiron is an asteroid known as the wounded healer and the descendant is our 7th house cusp of partnerships in a natal chart. the chiron person will either heal or hurt the descendant depending on the karma carried over from their past life together. 
more of their past life is revealed in their akashic records.

text:
už se nám zase blíží vánoce a mnoho z vás už bylo donuceno zúčastnit se šíleně trapnýho firmního večírku, kde se na sebe všichni tváří, že se mají rádi, šéfovi se leze do prdele až to hezký neni a ten největší suchar z kanceláře to pod náporem alkoholu a lehkých drog roztočí na tanečním parketu za (ne)rytmického tleskání přiopilejch matek od rodin, aby se nakonec za rohem vykousnul s tou divnou puritánkou z účtárny, která za celej večer neřekla ani slovo a jenom se nepřítomně rozhlíží po okolí. mezi tím se někam ztratil šéf a jedna ta zasloužilá mamina, která při každý příležitosti hájí rovnoprávnost žen, obdivuje #metoo a kategoricky odsuzuje sledování porna jako neodpustitelnou nevěru - ona by totiž svýmu miláčkovi nikdy nezahnula ani v myšlenkách. ehm... v pondělí se většina firmy tváří, jako že žádnej večírek nebyl. ti, kteří odjeli domů před půlnocí vlastním autem se snaží zjistit, jaký to bylo potom, ale nějak se o tom nikomu nechce mluvit. a tak je to každej rok pořád dokola... na konci vesmíru si jeden takovej večírek taky uděláme, ale my máme fištróna - pokusíme se tu donebevolající trapnost vytvořit už od začátku, abychom předešli případným trapným momentům. paradoxně se tím všichni více uvolníme a zábava pak nabyde volnějších forem a pubertální představy nabydou konkrétních rozměrů. ❗️❗️❗️ v rámci autentičnosti je žádoucí, abychom každý zaujali svou roli, ke které samozřejmě patří i slušivý společenský oděv.
⚠️👔 takže suit up a welcome drink tě nemine! 🎁 a protože vánoce budou za pár dnů, bylo by vhodné se navzájem obdarovat. ze severního pólu máme přislíbeno, že pošlou santu 🎅, který tu velkou hromadu dárků rozdá. naprosto random. ano, znamená to, že dárečkem, který přinesete, bude obdarován zcela náhodně někdo jiný (který také nějaký dáreček donesl). kreativitě se meze nekladou, takže můžete přinést naprosto cokoli vás napadne nebo vám doma překáží, čímž si zajistíte své místo mezi obdarovanými. 🎵 k tomu samozřejmě proběhne pořádná firemní diskotéka, o kterou se postará dj nsrs.

a vzhledem k našemu generátoru nekonečné nepravděpodobnosti se to může zvrhnout v naprosto cokoli.  #porocevanoce #vanoce #mejdan #nakoncivesmiru #plzeň

text:
cyntoia brown, a 16 year old sex-trafficking victim, was sentenced to life in prison with the possibility of parole after 51 years, for killing her predator. that statement alone should rock you. never should a minor be sentenced for protecting themselves from a predator. with the wave of news about predators getting off with light sentences, it makes you wonder if our system values predators more than victims. 
is our justice system responsible for coddling predators?? whatever the answer is, cyntoia needs to be freed.

text:
"mira como nos ponemos... a facturar"

hoy en día hay mucho opinologo/a con postura o loros repitiendo la frase de turno y los más vivos sacando ganancia para su bolsillo.
la mayoría toma postura cayendo en una justicia social. acusando sin dejar a la justicia ejercer su labor. si el acusado es o no culpable lo determinará la justicia.

pero no vaya ser que si  de ser declarado inocente por la justicia sea un morgan freeman más, desprestigiando su carrera con falsas acusaciones .

o usar el cinismo como lo hizo una de las creadoras del movimiento #metoo asia argento que tuvo que cerrar la boca con plata porque se comprobó ante la justicia que se metió con un menor y este tenía fotos y chats que comprobaban el delito de abuso sexual.

si sufrís un abuso sexual denuncia!! seas hombre o mujer. denuncia ante la justicia no ante una cámara, twitter, facebook, instagram y demás red social. denuncia ante la justicia!!! #justicia #justiciasocial #miracomonosponemos #metoo #abusosexual #asiaargento #feminismoradical #feminismo #nadiemenos #niunamenos #thelmafardina #juandarthes

.

text: #noesno. a mis 15/6 años un hombre mayor de más de 40 intentó seducirme, era el guardia de seguridad del lugar en donde fuimos de campamento con el colegio. me invitó a salir y me dijo que estaba interesado en mí y que me quería conocer. mágicamente pude "controlar" la situación y logré salir del cuarto (cocina) en el que estábamos sin que me hiciera nada. sabía que eso estaba mal y hablé se lo conté a todos, les mostré la nota que me había dado e hice que lo despidieran. no tengan miedo de hablar, cada vez nos hacemos más fuertes! . #noesno #miracomonosponemos #basta #metoo #estamostodasjuntas #sevaacaer ✊💪

dairy’s dark secret
the typical dairy cow on a farm produces nearly 22,000 pounds of milk a year – more than double­ what its forebears did 40 years ago. they never graze; their hooves have rotted from standing in their own filth. 
_
cows, like pigs, are social creatures; their babies are even more so. they nuzzle strangers, groan with pleasure when you pet them, and attach without complaint to callous minders. their sweetness gets them nowhere at auctions or at farms, however; the men and women working here smack them with boards and kick them in the haunches to move them forward. as one undercover investigator stated; “so common,” “seen guys punch them, stick cattle prods in their eyes, bragging, ‘i totally got her in the eyeball!’ it’s what happens when you do this long enough. they’re not your fellow creatures, they’re just trouble.
_
then there's the baby...a calf that can’t get up. its velveteen eyes are wet but blank; he barely stirs when jostled by other calves. “he got sick and gave up,” and so it goes with farmers who gave up farming to become cruel jailers of their "stock". it’s like they hate their own animals for having feelings.”
_
how can you possibly justify this for a glass of milk, a piece of cheese, a bowl of #icecream?there are so many plant-based alternatives available. please choose wisely. will your choices be responsible for creating more victims?
_

text:
the most hardest thing this year had been is..staying strong😞💛
i had a lot of ups and downs.  mostly downs. it's very personal but at the same time it's out too much too hide. i had the most struggling year of my life emotionally. i don't know if it taught me anything or not but it did make me go through a lot.
▶from my father's sudden second marriage and leaving us to the most extreme heartbreak ever felt💔 from seeing my mom in extreme pain to losing people around me for life💔 from having serious depression to having no friends left at all in need💔 this year has got the worst around me.
during this time, i had a lot of thoughts💭 i had thoughts like giving up (if you know what i'm saying exactly) and i had thoughts like running away. i did. but in the end of day, i chose to pretend and smile all the time and fool people around me into believing that i'm fine💜 mostly people believed too. it's crazy.
.
.
wanna take a small moment to appreciate myself for still staying strong enough. still surviving. this is my favourite picture cuz its showing the fake happiness so perfectly and hiding the crying face at every night and all the dark circle it gave me.
.
.
you all will be seeing a lot of changing in my lifestyle now and i'm really excited to share what this whole year has turned me going towards to🌹
thank you allah for giving me such strength ♥

text:
there's this girl who met me some 8 years ago and even today is always there when i need her the most. we live so away from each other... you can say in two different countries, yes! she's married, she has a cute kid. she is so occupied with her family. yet, whenever i feel low, she's always at a distance of a call... one single call. ❤️ ayesha @esh0623 has met me for the least number of days and even today, i find in her, a friend, a guide, a support for lifetime.

she's the kind of friend who has been with me from my first heartbreak to my greatest problems regarding life and career.

this message is to show my love for her.

ayesha, i love you so much honey. you are one of a kind. ❤️ - from swarada @d_arcane_pneuma 
_________________________________

in these times of #metoo and stories of sexual harassment, there are also women and men around us who made us feel more beautiful, more confident and powerful from both inside and out. 
if there is such a person in your life who ever made you feel so about yourself then wait no longer and share your story too. let us pay a small tribute to her/him here @shespeaksforthechange.

we all need such people around us afterall, don't we?
(dm us your story or tag us in your post.) #shespeaksforthechange #womensupportingwomen

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
si sta diffondendo in queste ore, ed è già stato definito il “metoo” del sudamerica.
l’hashtag #miracomonosponemos (letteralmente “guarda come ci hai fatte diventare”) è la reazione partita dalle donne argentine alla vicenda della loro connazionale thelma fardin, l’attrice oggi ventiseienne che molti ricorderanno come giusy de “il mondo di patty”. in un video, pubblicato sul suo instagram due giorni fa e diventato presto virale, è infatti lei a denunciare il collega juan darthés (leandro nella stessa soap opera), accusandolo di averla violentata mentre i due lavoravano ad un tour dello show.

all’epoca dell’abuso, racconta, lei aveva 16 anni e lui 45. la testimonianza è davvero straziante, scende nei dettagli, cita le parole di lui che prima di forzarla fisicamente la incolpava per la propria erezione, dicendole “guarda cosa mi hai fatto”. parole che, appunto, ora vengono ribaltate nel loro significato.
darthés, che dal canto suo nega le accuse, è stato formalmente denunciato.
ieri ha avuto luogo una conferenza, alla presenza del collettivo actrices argentinas, che ha visto la partecipazione della stessa fardin.

proprio come per il #metoo, c’è chi mette in dubbio la validità del movimento, perché ancora non esistono prove concrete a supporto del racconto di thelma.
proprio come per il #metoo, noi diamo invece già ora il nostro pieno supporto, per una ragione che ci preme ricordare: i dati statistici parlano di denunce di violenza che si rivelano vere nel 98% dei casi; thelma è il volto più riconoscibile del movimento, ma non l’unico. dietro a questo hashtag c’è la risposta ad un sistema, c’è un “fronte comune” con cui incoraggiare tante vittime a chiedere giustizia.

text:
“women are awful to each other”
“i just prefer male friends”
“i can’t make women friends”

every woman has female friend trauma, whether that’s information betrayed, women leaving us or just being drained from a night of complaining.  i have said every one of those things and hear women every day ache for friendship. 
maya angelou wrote, “have the courage to trust love one more time.  and always one more time.” not just romantic love but sister love. 
it is possible to get beyond the catty complaining pretend intimacy that so many women do.  you know how?  healing trauma.  because when we come into a friendship trauma informed we can love and support and encourage with a gentle ferocity not experienced today. 
i didn’t trust women and had lots of evidence to avoid female friendships at all costs.  and now i am surrounded by women who inspire, love, support. 
trauma informed, sobriety informed fierce loyal love ❤️💗🌈. these friendships can heal.  not just us but our communities, our families and the planet. 
if you’re ready for community, sisterhood and a community of women who has got your back, ignite the fire may be for you.  let’s get on a call and talk about it. link in the comments 🌈🦄💕 you’re safe here and there are women aching for your friendship too.

text:
shana began cans for karma in 2011. when pregnant with her first child, she saw the need to educate her daughter on service and giving to her community. since then, shana and her daughters have hosted a food and supply drive every year. 
they have give to 180 place; the last 3 years have been dedicated to donating to my sister's house. shana realized the importance of serving women and children in dire need and shifted the focus of cans for karma. 
she reaches out to her family and friends through word-of-mouth and social media posts. friends contact her to arrange a pickup or drop off, meeting time and location, and she and her daughters store and arrange the donations in their own home. 
eight years ago, the first drive was enough to fit on a beverage cart. this latest drive garnered so much support, two vans were used to transport the goods to msh. 
she hopes to continue her family's service to the community each year by hosting cans for karma.

text:
monster_aileen wuornos (1/3)

hello folks, it's #monologuethursday! it's crazy, but we are already over 40 - f o r t y - thursdays spent together, and i couldn't be more grateful for the love and support you showed me all along ❤
this week i am proposing you this monologue from monster, which i find particularly heartbreaking because behind those words i see the little girl talking, dreaming that one day someone will see her potential and will save her from her life. but no. hope is weakness. trust is weakness. and ultimately, if you are weak you will succumb. and even when you will decide you will rebel to that, you will fail.
the consequences of abuse are multiple and last forever, and the story of aileen popped up in my mind after reading the words of the victim of jacob walter anderson's assault, how that stripped her confidence away and changed her life forever- but still, he won't go to jail for that. and then i thought of cyntoia brown, who will go to jail for murdering the man who made her a sex slave. and then i thought of all the #metoo survivors and of the poisonous reactions to their statements. 
the war on women's bodies is strong, and as any war the consequences are terrible and long lasting, and the collateral damage is incalculable.
because sending to jail cyntoia for murdering that man may be technically legally correct, but it's not right, nor just.
and i'm not comparing their stories, but if we have to "like" the victim to really see the abuser for what he is, then we are even worse that we think we are.
love

text:
el movimiento #metoo ha cruzado la frontera #argentina. el desgarrador testimonio de la intérprete @soythelmafardín sobre su presunta violación a manos del cantante y actor @juandarthesok ha provocado un revuelo en el que hasta el gobierno argentino ha intervenido.
tras conocer la denuncia de fardín, conocida por su papel en la exitosa serie patito feo, las autoridades han decidido retirar un vídeo promocional contra la violencia de género en el que aparecía darthés. “si te dice que no, es no”, decía el anuncio.
el actor acaba de ser denunciado ante la justicia de #nicaragua por presuntamente protagonizar una de las formas más extremas de violencia contra la mujer: la violación a una menor. otras tres actrices lo habían acusado previamente de acoso.
en 2007, formó parte de la serie juvenil patito feo, que se convirtió en un éxito continental y llevó a sus actores de gira por varios países latinoamericanos. darthés era el único adulto de un elenco en el que estaban brenda asnicar y thelma fardín, entre otras actrices adolescentes. arropada por compañeros de profesión, fardín reveló en una rueda de prensa que tenía 16 años cuando el actor, entonces 45, la violó en un hotel en nicaragua.
tras anunciarlo, miles de argentinos se volcaron con ella en las redes sociales bajo la etiqueta #mirácómonosponemos, en lo que los medios han bautizado como el capítulo argentino del movimiento #metoo.
por su lado, darthés negó la acusación e inició un juicio por das y perjuicios contra ella que aún está en curso. #latribunapanamá mj

text:
el movimiento #metoo ha cruzado la frontera #argentina. el desgarrador testimonio de la intérprete @soythelmafardín sobre su presunta violación a manos del cantante y actor @juandarthesok ha provocado un revuelo en el que hasta el gobierno argentino ha intervenido.
tras conocer la denuncia de fardín, conocida por su papel en la exitosa serie patito feo, las autoridades han decidido retirar un vídeo promocional contra la violencia de género en el que aparecía darthés. “si te dice que no, es no”, decía el anuncio.
el actor acaba de ser denunciado ante la justicia de #nicaragua por presuntamente protagonizar una de las formas más extremas de violencia contra la mujer: la violación a una menor. otras tres actrices lo habían acusado previamente de acoso.
en 2007, formó parte de la serie juvenil patito feo, que se convirtió en un éxito continental y llevó a sus actores de gira por varios países latinoamericanos. darthés era el único adulto de un elenco en el que estaban brenda asnicar y thelma fardín, entre otras actrices adolescentes. arropada por compañeros de profesión, fardín reveló en una rueda de prensa que tenía 16 años cuando el actor, entonces 45, la violó en un hotel en nicaragua.
tras anunciarlo, miles de argentinos se volcaron con ella en las redes sociales bajo la etiqueta #mirácómonosponemos, en lo que los medios han bautizado como el capítulo argentino del movimiento #metoo.
por su lado, darthés negó la acusación e inició un juicio por das y perjuicios contra ella que aún está en curso. #noticias7días mj

text:
appetit fait sa xmast party ! ce soir 🌲🌲🌲 parce que la cuisine, c’est beaucoup d’amour…
parce que l’amour, ça met en appétit…
parce que noël, c’est le moment idéal pour se réconcilier autour de la cuisine, on a préparé pour vous plein de surprises à prix tout doux.
dans la hotte d'appétit il y a : les conffetis, la revue des femmes inspirées et inspirantes, des cadeaux pour les belles mères adorables, les gendres éco-responsables, les frères flexitariens, les soeurs qui n'aiment rien, les amateurs de vin ... cerise sur le sapin fiona schmidt et emmanuelle teyras dédicaceront à quatre mains leurs oeuvres complètes : 
les recettes d’une connasse, qu'est ce qu'on mange ?, l’amour après #metoo, 40 ans, what the f... ! 
il y aura nos amis, il y aura vos amis et beaucoup, beaucoup de bonnes ondes !
venez ! 
la xmast party c'est jeudi 13 décembre à partir de 18h30 chez appetit,12 rue jean ferrandi 75006
#amis #paris #noel #magazine #fete #appetitparis #cookbook #beauxlivres #confettis

text:
«je n’ai ni violé, ni pillé, ni torturé ni traumatisé les femmes. c'était les générations passées. c'était son ex. c'était son père. pourquoi est-ce que c'est à moi de supporter le choc de son traumatisme, de sa rage et de sa méfiance ? ». la réponse est simple : c'est là où nous nous trouvons aujourd'hui. c'est le moment où nous sommes nés. chaque génération d'hommes doit faire face à une bataille karmique. ce mouvement #metoo, post-féministe est notre karma.⠀
⠀
assumer cette guérison du cœur, une femme à la fois, est le grand défi auquel sont confrontés les hommes dans le monde. ce n'est pas gagner plus d'argent. c'est n'est pas inventer le prochain miracle de technologie. ce n'est pas voyager dans les jungles du pérou pour expérimenter l'ayahuasca.⠀
⠀
une façon de réinventer notre relation avec le féminin consiste à visiter une magnifique forêt. l'élégance sauvage du pin immaculé, le soleil et le chant des oiseaux détendent immédiatement votre système nerveux. l'air est frais et la beauté luxuriante nourrit votre cœur et votre âme. maintenant, imaginez que vous tombiez sur des canettes de bière, des cartouches et du plastique jetés près d'un feu de camp construit à la hâte. vous pourriez être légèrement agacé.⠀
⠀
mais vous pensez : « je pourrais nettoyer cela, mais quelle différence cela ferait-il. je n’ai pas fait ça. ce n'est pas ma responsabilité. » il existe probablement des centaines de piles d'ordures, le plus souvent laissées par des hommes, éparpillées dans la forêt. plutôt que de simplement hausser les épaules et de continuer votre chemin sur des espaces moins contaminés de la forêt, qu’arriverait-il si vous emballiez tout ce que vous pouviez et qu'à la place vous laissiez une offrande de cône de pins, de galets et de fleurs magnifiquement organisée ?⠀
⠀
sentez maintenant les similitudes de cette forêt avec le cœur d'une femme que vous aimez. y a-t-il des cicatrices laissées par des amants antérieurs ou d’autres hommes sous la forme de traumatismes, d’abus et de négligence ?⠀
⠀
pourriez-vous vous engager, comme dans la nature, à nettoyer les débris et à y laisser une bénédiction à la place ?"⠀
- john wineland ⠀
⠀
suite sur le blog/page fb

text:
we talk about empowering girls, we share impacting and inspiring videos, articles on various topics related to gender equality, violence, etc. we all voiced out for #metoo. when you do all this, what stops you from taking the next step - action. our empower workshop is conceptualized to equip the young girls & women of all ages basic self-defense techniques, equipping them to fight back both mentally & physically during untoward situations. 
knowing how to identify a suspicious situation and protecting yourself from it could be a life-saving tool in event of an attack, that's why we at aware encourage women to dedicate a few hours to learn basic self-defense. we teach women and girls how to be better aware of their surroundings and go over basic moves that could help save their lives.

join us to learn how you can defend yourself in similar situations. 
share the stage with like-minded women and find your super power. *#nomorenirbhaya- an aware initiative* *date:* 16th december, sunday
*time:* 10 am to 1 pm
_exact venue will be shared with the registered participants_

_registration is free, but mandatory. register @ bit.ly/emp16dec or via whatsapp "nomorenirbhaya" to 8122241688_

let's build a better society where every girl and woman feel safe, empowered and respected!

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
congratulations janet!

janet jackson inducted into the rock ‘n roll hall of fame.

the latest batch of rock and roll hall of fame inductees were announced thursday morning on siriusxm’s volume channel, and the class of 2019 is a straight-a lineup, featuring deserving — and sometimes previously ludicrously overlooked — luminaries of r&b (janet jackson), post-punk (the cure), metal (def leppard), alternative (radiohead), glam (roxy music), and classic rock (the zombies, stevie nicks). janet jackson’s inclusion is especially exciting. in the #metoo era, it seems like all the world has been rallying around miss jackson — whose career stalled after the “nipplegate” scandal at super bowl lii (reportedly due to the dastardly scheming of disgraced cbs executive les moonves), while her equally responsible halftime duet partner, justin timberlake, walked away unscathed. jackson’s recent politically charged “state of the world” tour was a massive success; she recently received the icon award at the billboard music awards; and she’s finally being rightfully heralded as the forerunner to triple-threat divas like beyoncé and rihanna. her hall induction is the perfect way for the three-time rock hall nominee to complete her comeback story arc.
name: Abdur-Rahim Briggs
