text:
thelma fardin, l'attrice argentina de il mondo di patty, ha rotto il silenzio che manteneva da dieci anni e ha denunciato un collega attore, juan darthes, accusandolo di averla violentata in nicaragua quando lei aveva 16 anni e lui 45. thelma fardin fa parte dell'associazione "attrici argentine", che ha lanciato "niunamenos", la versione argentina del #metoo. darthes ha negato ogni accusa e poco dopo è stato ricoverato in ospedale per un malore.

l'attrice ha avuto il coraggio di denunciarlo durante un'assemblea in un teatro della capitale, dopo un'altra denuncia da parte dell'attrice @lacalurivero , "emma" della stessa fiction, quando l'uomo avrebbe toccato la collega andando ben oltre il ruolo, dopodiché quest'ultima si é licenziata.

tornando dalla piscina mi sono accorta che mi si era smagnetizzata la scheda per aprire la porta dell'hotel", ha ricordato thelma, aggiungendo che "lui mi ha detto: perché non vieni in camera mia e
chiedi per telefono che te ne portino un'altra?". "accettai - ha aggiunto - ma mentre ero al telefono ha cominciato a baciarmi sul collo e non si è fermato più". il video racconta tutti i particolari della violenza interrotta solo quando qualcuno bussò alla porta, e dedica le ultime sequenze ai volti delle attrici solidali che guardando fissa la telecamera sfidano lo stupratore. durante la conferenza stampa è poi emerso che darthes ha perfino partecipato alla realizzazione di uno spot del ministero dello sviluppo sociale contro la violenza di genere, che ora l'istituto nazionale delle donne ha deciso di ritirare da tutti i suoi social network.

tutto ciò é inammissibile. tutti i giorni stanno succedono queste terribili vicende ed é arrivata l'ora di alzarci e denunciare! parlare! siamo tutti uniti per sconfiggere la violenza, quella sulle donne, sugli uomini, sui bambini, sugli animali.la violenza.
non dobbiamo assolutamente arrenderci! ¡mira como nos podemos! @soythelmafardin @patitofeoserie15 @laura_esquivel #miracomonospodemos #thelmafardin #juandarthes #patitofeo #ilmondodipatty #telenovela #argentina

text:
i decided to start my own (beginner friendly) writing blog. i've been writing heavily since i was 13 years old, and i've learned much from being in the writing community for 3 1/3 years at the collegiate level.
-
the most important thing you need to do is start; it doesn't matter where, as long as you just do. it doesn't matter what you think you content is worth, because you aren't writing to please anyone else, correct? you're writing from your heart to ease your mind or vice versa. the opinions of others never matter, because you can always improve and reach across several different genres. -
i have several more articles ready to publish, but i really want you to start from the beginning. i want you to hear me out when i tell you that these instructions are necessary. the purpose of this blog is to get your feet firmly planted within the world of writing. i will get you from daydreamer to published author, at your own pace of course. -
-
all of the current available blog posts are at the link in my bio. take some time out of your morning to read, digest, and apply these methods to your daily writing routine. in the long-run, you'll thank yourself for taking your writing seriously. -
i also have written several tens of articles on medium, which are also available on my website. they contain key elements to success when publishing your content.💛

text: tempers flared during a recent interview between kodak black and ebro, prompting the dying to live rapper to cut the conversation short. though kodak originally stopped by to discuss his upcoming album, the hot 97 host closed the conversation by addressing black’s upcoming sexual assault trial. “it’s good to meet you man,” starts ebro, clearly sitting on the inevitable bomb drop. “looking at all your cases man, and everything you’ve been through, and i know the recent one is very sensitive. with respect to everybody involved in that case, and we can’t get into details, but we take sexual assault very serious. we can’t get into details, but we hope to have you back so we can have a deeper conversation about that, because it’s a serious topic. we’re hearing these stories a lot.” the speech prompts an uncomfortable silence from kodak, who appears visibly angered by ebro’s words. his seething does not go unnoticed, as ebro, somewhat aggressively, observes that kodak seems upset that it was brought up at all. the subsequent cuts to rosenberg and laura are unintentionally comedic in their awkwardness, though kodak is far from amused. ebro merely stares on, challenging the rapper. “i feel like,” says kodak, shifting uncomfortably. “sometimes when n***s like me going through shit, ya’ll be entertained by bullshit. change the subject or i finna walk out.” rosenberg attempts to keep the peace, but ebro’s mind is made up. “we don’t have to talk about nothing else,” says ebro. “we can be done right here.” kodak agrees, and proceeds to walk out. as they cut to “commercial,” ebro can be heard declaring “you won’t tell me what to talk about on my show.” while not quite birdman on breakfast club levels of awkwardness, it certainly toes the line. ebro took to twitter to address the debacle, in a series of tweets . as we know, kodak black is currently awaiting trial for sexual assault, which is set to take place in april 2019. peep the video and tweets in the full story at www.itskenbarbie.com (or swipe) do you think ebro was out of line or kodak? #kodak #kodakblack #kodakblackalert #ebro #ebrointhemorning #hot97 #metoo #entertainment #entertainmentnews

we are encouraging community members and hutton house participants to take part in a very important community project, #safecityldn 
this project focuses on mapping our city with areas we feel unsafe in. the intent is to identify these locations in our city and create a safer environment for our london community members based on your input. 
please use your voice to speak up about #sexualharassment by heading to the safe city london website. 
the deadline for this initiative is #december 31st 2018! so be sure to get mapping before the new year arrives!

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
do not be fooled, do not complex, do not compare yourself to others, you are beautiful in your way, you will always be beautiful for someone. today if we have so many pictures of ourselves, it's thanks to makeup filters, photoshop etc. today i show you my face without filter, without makeup to show you the truth. you are beautiful. we are beautiful and unique because these eyebrows not brushed are mine, these dark circles too, ... all this belong to me. something we can not copy.
🍓
🍓
🍓
ne te fais pas avoir, ne complexe pas, ne te compares pas aux autres, tu es belle à ta manière, tu seras toujours belle pour quelqu'un. aujourd'hui si on a autant de photos de nous même c'est grâce aux filtres aux maquillages, à photoshop etc. 
aujourd'hui je te montre mon visage sans filtre, sans maquillage pour te montrer que la vérité. tu es belle. on est belle et unique car ces sourcils pas brossé sont à moi, ces cernes aussi,... tout ceci m'appartiens. quelque chose qu'on ne peut pas copier.

commentaire.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

svart bälte i solidaritet, det kan man säga att luciatåget i vårgårda har. 🤜💥🤛 eftersom luciadagen är på en torsdag i år passar följet på att uppmärksamma #thursdaysinblack genom att byta ut det röda bandet mot svart. torsdagar i svart är en global fredlig protest mot våld och våldtäkt särskilt i konfliktdrabbade områden. den initierades av kyrkornas världsråd på 1980-talet. "vi tycker det här passar ihop med lucia som skyddshelgon för svaga grupper i samhället. hennes livsgärning och död har ju blivit en symbol för våld mot kvinnor, och det är en referenspunkt som känns central idag", säger josefin roos som bär luciakrona på bilden.

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

svart bälte i solidaritet, det kan man säga att luciatåget i vårgårda har. 🤜💥🤛 eftersom luciadagen är på en torsdag i år passar följet på att uppmärksamma #thursdaysinblack genom att byta ut det röda bandet mot svart. torsdagar i svart är en global fredlig protest mot våld och våldtäkt särskilt i konfliktdrabbade områden. den initierades av kyrkornas världsråd på 1980-talet. "vi tycker det här passar ihop med lucia som skyddshelgon för svaga grupper i samhället. hennes livsgärning och död har ju blivit en symbol för våld mot kvinnor, och det är en referenspunkt som känns central idag", säger josefin roos som bär luciakrona på bilden.

text: #tbt do dia que lançamos ela da @cervejaporelas - na época (2016) fomos tão criticadas simplesmente por mulheres cervejeiras se unirem pra criarem um coletivo feminino e também por fazer uma cerveja pra comemorar o fato. a cerveja teve todo seu lucro revertido pra uma ong que ajuda mulheres. mesmo assim, as críticas, ofensas disfarçadas de brincadeirinhas, não pararam. hoje ainda mantemos o grupo como interno principalmente para nossas conversas e desabafos. o grupo é necessário ainda mais hoje com os maiores desaforos, loucuras e total falta de noção de direitos humanos dos nossos governantes atuais e futuros. é triste ver que parece que a equidade de gênero ainda é um sonho. nossa luta está cada vez mais difícil, ainda mais depois dos últimos dias com a “bolsa estupro “. tá phoda. mas não desisto. foto do meu amado amigo @ifgolfetto 😘 #ninguemsoltaamãodeninguem #feminismo  #cervejaporelas #meucorpominhasregras #foraministra #womanempowerment #metoo #timesupnow #feminism

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian
